title: hot bittersweet sauce
directions: Melt the butter or oleo and chocolate in a saucepan until smooth over low heat.
Stir in the cocoa, sugar, cream and salt. Bring slowly to just a boil; do not stir.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and serve warm.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to the soft ball stage at 238°. Add peanuts and salt.
Cook to hard crack, 290°.
Remove from heat and add butter and soda.
Stir well.
Pour into greased platter. Cool by lifting around edge.
When cool, but still slightly warm, turn over.
Break into pieces.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Mix and cool 20 minutes before baking.
Drop on greased pan. Decorate and bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate nut dainties
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt in a small pan 1/2 bag chocolate chips and 1/4 cup butter.
Set aside for use as the coating.
Sift flour and salt on waxed paper.
Beat together margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate pieces (other 1/2 bag).
Shape mixture into "logs" which are 2-inches long and 1/2-inch in diameter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
After cooling, dip each end into the coating and then the crushed walnuts.
Cool and serve. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spread on tortillas and roll. Refrigerate overnight in a covered container. Slice in 1-inch pieces and serve. Makes 6 to 8 (10-inch) rolls.

title: lay-by slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Layer cabbage, onion and bell pepper in a large bowl.
Pour 1 cup sugar over top; do not stir.
Boil vinegar, oil, dry mustard, celery seed and salt.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: strawberry cookies
directions: In a skillet, mix the butter, egg, dates, coconut, sugar and salt. Cook on a medium-low heat 5 to 10 minutes or until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Cool 10 minutes or until mixture can be handled. Shape into a cone.
Roll cone in red sugar. Add green frosting on top.

title: baked corn
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients in small amount of butter.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over corn and stir.
Fold in 2 eggs whites.
Pour into well-buttered casserole dish.
Bake in pie pan of water for 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove pan of water and bake 15 minutes at 350° to brown.

title: crab imperial
directions: Rinse, drain and flake crabmeat.
Prepare gravy mix according to package directions.
Mix lightly with crabmeat, mayonnaise, mushrooms, parsley and lemon juice.
Spoon into shallow buttered casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: elegant chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Melt Hershey bars.
Cool to lukewarm and add vanilla.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour to butter and egg mixture.
Add melted chocolate.
Bake in tube pan at 320° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: lemony cheesecake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Set aside.

title: soft spice bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine margarine, 1 cup sugar and molasses.
Beat in egg until smooth. Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices; stir into the molasses mixture.
Spread into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Do not overbake.
Cool on a wire rack before cutting. Yield:
2 1/2 dozen.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Store in airtight container.
Makes approximately 3 cups dry mixture.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream well sugar, oleo and Crisco.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, to mixture.
Add flour and buttermilk.
Fold in well.
Beat egg whites and add with coconut and pecans to mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown about 25 minutes.

title: eggplant pie
directions: Place eggplant and tomatoes on bottom of cookie sheet.
Place onion and pepper on top of tomatoes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle a little oil on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tuna vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Place potatoes in a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with rosemary and pepper.
Combine milk and gravy mix.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: luncheon tuna salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf, if desired.

title: chinese spareribs
directions: Place side of ribs on a rack in a large, flat pan.
Place 2 plus cups of water in the pan and cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Place on the stove under high heat.
When steaming, reduce heat to low-medium and parboil for 45 minutes.
Combine the remaining ingredients, except honey.
When ribs are done, cut them using a sharp knife.
Place them in a marinating dish and cover with the marinade for a minimum of 5 hours.
Turn the ribs every few hours.

title: carrot-pecan cookies
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cardamom and cinnamon; set aside.
In a second bowl, beat butter with brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla extract and beat well.
Add flour mixture in 2 or 3 batches.
Stir in carrots, pecans and raisins.
Drop by tablespoons, 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: tarragon dip
directions: Mix all together; chill.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine cornbread mix and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients then add to cornbread mixture, beat just enough to moisten thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned with edges pulling away from side of pan.
Best if served warm. 18 to 24 servings.

title: rachel's easy pie
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix together sugar, flour, milk and egg.
Pour into dish containing melted margarine.
Pour fruit filling into middle of dish containing other ingredients.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 45 minutes until brown.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake a white cake as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan. While it is hot, puncture holes in top of cake. Pour cream de coconut over cake, then Eagle Brand milk. Spread pineapple over the cake. Ice cake with Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut over top. Chill before serving.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake until knife comes out clean.

title: cuban chicken fricassee
directions: Heat olive oil in medium heat in a large saucepan.
Add chicken breast, salt, cumin, garlic powder, potatoes, bell pepper and onion.
Stir until chicken turns white.
Add cooking wine, tomato sauce, water, bouillon cube and cilantro.
Cook until potatoes become soft, about 30 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses.
Add beaten eggs. Add flour to make a good batter.
Add spices.
Mix soda in sour milk.
Add.
Mix well.
Bake in moderate oven about 30 minutes. Test with toothpick.
If it comes out clean and shrinks from sides of pan, it is done.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix according to directions for the cake mix.
Divide batter in half and bake in 2 pans.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cake will be about 1-inch thick.
While cake is baking, mix evaporated milk in sugar.
Bring to rapid boil.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Add coconut.
Pour over 2 cakes.

title: candy cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine.
Boil 3 minutes then add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
May be eaten with 1/2 hour after making.
Keep in cool place and an airtight container.

title: old tyme chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar and eggs. Alternate adding flour and milk.
Mix well and pour into 8 inch cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: kathy's chewy excellent brownies
directions: Beat together eggs, butter and vanilla.
Mix together cocoa, flour and sugar.
Add moist ingredients to dry and stir well.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes in greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: green beans
directions: Steam the beans until crisp or soft, your choice. Drizzle with olive oil, salt, pepper and garlic parsley blend. Toss together and serve.

title: grilled corn-on-the-cob
directions: Peel husks back just enough to remove silk.
Return husks to their original position.
In a sink or large kettle, soak corn covered in water for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Grill corn on an uncovered grill directly over medium-hot coals for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender, turning often.

title: microwave spaghetti
directions: Place butter and onion in pan.
Heat on Full power for 3 to 4 minutes, until onion is tender.
Add beef; cook on Full power for 4 minutes, until beef is no longer pink.
Stir twice during cooking time.
Add salt, pepper, sauce, water, oregano and basil. Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Break spaghetti and stir into sauce and cook 18 to 20 minutes, until spaghetti is tender.
Stir 3 times during cooking.
If desired, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix flour, nuts and oleo.
Spread evenly on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool.

title: almost wild rice
directions: Melt oleo; break vermicelli into oleo and brown.
Add rice, mushrooms, onion, consomme, salt and pepper and add 1 cup water. Cover and cook, stirring as necessary, for 20 minutes or until almost dry, then add last cup of water.
Simmer until dry, about 30 minutes.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients including juice in minced clams.
Heat at 350° in oven until bubbly.
Serve with crackers, bread sticks and chips.
Delicious.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.

title: holiday cheese potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes.
While potatoes are still hot, add all ingredients, except bacon.
Stir with wooden spoon until of spreading consistency.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until bubbly and bacon is crisp.
Excellent for holiday dinners.
Can be made the day before, except for adding the bacon crumbles.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk, egg yolk and vanilla.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture begins to thicken, add margarine.
Filling is done when thick and forms a peak.
Use egg whites to make meringue for top.
Brown meringue in oven.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except corn chips and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Slightly crush 2 cups corn chips and add to meat mixture.
Put into 8-inch square pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining corn chips and cheese.
Return to the oven for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: lentil soup
directions: A goodly sized piece of left over ham to add to a ham hock, add salt and cover with water and simmer for 2 hours, remove meat from the bones and add it to the broth along with one pound of dry split peas, one large chopped onion and 1/4 teaspoon of garlic powder.
Simmer for 3 or 4 hours stirring frequently.
Serve with a dollop of whipped cream or a sprinkle of parmesan cheese and a dash of paprika.

title: chocolate mocha cake
directions: Cream the Crisco.
Add sugar and beaten egg.
Dissolve soda and cocoa in sour milk.
Add to the mixture.
Stir in flour slowly.
Beat 100 times.
Place in well-greased pan and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: sunday oven fried potatoes - justin's favorite
directions: Wash potatoes and boil about 30 minutes.
Cool.
Peel or leave skins on as you desire.
Cut in lengthwise wedges.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Brush over potatoes.
Spray pan with cooking spray and also spray on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: golden lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then flour.
Melt butter in skillet. Brown chicken over medium heat, 4 minutes, turning once.
Stir in golden herb lemon soup mix, blended with water.
Put lemon slice on each piece of chicken.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, 10 minutes until sauce thickens and chicken is done. Serve over hot rice, spooning sauce over chicken.
Makes 4 servings. Very good!

title: just like orange julius(also known as frothy orange drink)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in an electric blender and blend to desired consistency.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 2-quart casserole and stir.
Add peanuts and salt and cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir and cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook for 2 minutes and 40 seconds on High.
Add soda immediately and stir slowly and spread on lightly buttered cookie sheet.

title: one crust apple pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, salt, spices and flour.
Mix well and add apples and stir.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into apple mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: carol's chicago chili
directions: Lightly brown the ground beef, then add the chopped onions. Simmer for a few minutes.
Place all the ingredients into slow cooker.
Cook 9 to 10 hours on low setting.
After the allotted time, stir chili and check the seasonings.

title: tomato and pepper steak with rice
directions: Flour and salt steak.
Brown in bacon grease.
Remove steak and make loose gravy with flour, tomatoes and water.
Now return steak to gravy mixture.
Add peppers, bouillon cubes, soy sauce or Kitchen bouquet and onions.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes. (If gravy gets thick, add more water.)
Stir occasionally. Prepare rice according to directions.
Spread rice into a buttered 11 x 13-inch dish or large bowl.
Top rice with steak and gravy mixture.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk together until thick. Add pineapple, cherries, nuts and Cool Whip.
Blend in marshmallows and chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar; let stand.
Grate rind of 1 orange.
Add to cranberries.
Squeeze oranges; use juice and enough water to make 2 cups liquid.
Use this with boiling water to mix gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add cranberry mixture and apples.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish and chill until set.

title: macaroni and beef casserole
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook ground beef, green pepper, onion and seasonings until meat is browned (10 minutes).
Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Mix cooked macaroni, tomatoes with their liquid, meat and remaining ingredients, breaking up tomatoes.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until mixture is hot and bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: missionaries' berry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with a little more than half the pastry.
Lightly toss together the berries, cornstarch, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Fill the lined pie plate. Roll out the remaining pastry and cut a few slits in the top. Cover the fruit, sealing the edges well.
For a glossy crust, brush with cream or beaten egg yolks.
Bake for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: puttin on the ritz
directions: Spread Ritz crackers on baking sheet.
Combine condensed milk, dates and pecans in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Take a small spoon and put a small amount of pecan mixture on each Ritz cracker.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and cook in crock-pot on medium for 1 hour.
Can be baked in oven at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: lo-cal banana mocha cheesecake
directions: Bake 1 chocolate cake mix according to directions in a jelly roll pan; cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.

title: mexican salad
directions: Layer and toss.
If you want a dressing, use Catalina.
Good fresh or left over until the next day.
It is a meal alone. Serves 14 plus.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute sausage and ham in butter for 5 minutes.	Add chicken and brown sugar; cook 5 more minutes.
Add celery, bell pepper, onion; cook 5 minutes more.
Add all spices and saute 1 minute. Mix in tomatoes and garlic.
Cook for an additional minute or two. Combine everything with chicken stock and rice in a Dutch oven. Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until all liquid has been absorbed.

title: crumb topping for fruit
directions: Mix flour, sugar and oleo until crumbly.
Cover bottom of pan with any fresh fruit.
Top with crumbs.
Bake until brown in medium oven (350°).
Serve with whipped cream, Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: easy monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar in small bowl.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll into ball and then roll in sugar mixture.
Place sugared balls into Bundt pan and pour in butter.
Add brown sugar to remaining sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes,.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, mixing well.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all together and let set for a little while before frying in deep fat.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Do not salt.
Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into balls.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Balls can be frozen and baked later.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Put in a bowl; dig a well in center.
Pour in the oil.
Pour water over and mix well.
Add beaten eggs and pumpkin mix.
Pour into 3 medium sized loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend oil, zucchini and eggs in blender.
Pour into a bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veal with green noodles
directions: Brown veal in butter in ovenproof skillet.
Add onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook until onion is tender.
Blend in flour.
Add brandy and ignite.
When flame subsides, add broth.
Cover; bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add mushrooms, water chestnuts and cream.
Stir until blended.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over hot noodles.
Serves 6.

title: fruit bread pudding(use your favorite fruit when making this pudding.)
directions: In a large bowl, soak bread crumbs in milk for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, and mix well.
Place in a greased baking dish and cover.
Bake in a 300° oven for 25 minutes.
If desired, you can add a meringue topping and brown.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Mix according to directions.
Bake 20 minutes in a greased 11 x 17-inch cookie pan.

title: fruit pudding salad
directions: Sprinkle
pudding
over
fruit and stir gently.
Chill. Just before serving, slice bananas into other fruit.

title: liver onion patties
directions: Put meat through grinder (fine grind) with onion and crackers. Add slightly beaten eggs, milk and salt.
Drop into hot oil. Flatten with spatula and fry on each side until brown and crisp.

title: christmas red bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put into 2 small loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and roll in balls. Cool in refrigerator or freezer a short time. Heat chocolate bar, chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler. Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate mixture.

title: hot and tangy garlic chicken
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips.
Coat with mixture of 1 tablespoon cornstarch, sherry or water and garlic.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Combine next 3 ingredients, with remaining cornstarch; set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok or skillet.
Add chicken and stir-fry 3 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Heat remaining oil in same pan in skillet over high heat.
Add vegetables.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Return chicken to pan with broth mixture.
Cook, stirring until sauce boils and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soy sauce.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: chicken soup
directions: Rinse chicken in cold water. Remove excess fat and place chicken in a large pot with the 12 cups water; bring to a boil. With a metal spoon, skim off all foam. Add onions, parsley and salt or aromat and salt.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Remove chicken and cool.
Chop into small pieces. Add celery, carrots, warm water with bouillon cubes and pepper to the stock. Simmer for 40 minutes.
Add the noodles and chopped chicken the last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: chocolate crispies(1921)
directions: To melted chocolate, add butter, sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla, beating well.
Spread mixture on baking sheet, 12 x 16-inch, or in three pans, 8 x 8-inch.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in hot 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: nell's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together with mixer.
Place in buttered casserole dish.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Wash cukes, peel and slice paper thin into a bowl.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix well, turning slices over in the salt.
Put plate over cukes in bowl and press down.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Drain juice.

title: twice "baked" potatoes
directions: Cook raw potatoes at High 10 to 12 minutes; let stand 3 to 5 minutes after cooking.
You may need
to turn potatoes over after 5 to 6 minutes.
Cut a thin slice (lengthwise) from each potato. Scoop out cooked potato, leaving a thin shell.
In small bowl, combine potato, cottage cheese, oleo, egg, onion and milk mixture, salt and pepper; mix until smooth.
Spoon potato mixture into shell; sprinkle with paprika.
Arrange potatoes in a circle in a microwavable dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook at Medium 4 minutes.
Let stand uncovered 3 minutes before serving.
Contains approximately 2 to 3 grams fat per potato.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening and cool.
Add 1 cup sugar, molasses and egg. Mix well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to sugar mixture until blended.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until done.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Cook string beans; drain and put into casserole dish.
Add tomatoes, cooked hamburger and cheese.
Mix Jiffy corn bread mix as directed on box.
Spread on top of other ingredients; bake in 375° oven until corn bread mix is golden brown.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together.
Mix next 4 ingredients together and add to dry mixture.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into casserole and bake in 1-inch hot water 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Mix apple slices and cranberries; sprinkle with sugar.
Spread in a 7 x 11-inch or 9-inch square pan.
Melt margarine; add oatmeal, flour, brown sugar and pecans.
Mix together and spread on the fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: super chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Cut 4 squares of the chocolate into 1/2-inch chunks; set aside.
Beat butter and sugars, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chocolate chunks and walnuts.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheets. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes, then remove from cookie sheets.
Melt remaining 4 squares chocolate.
Spread top half of each cookie.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
In separate bowl, mix together, mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Combine all ingredients together and marinate in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: dream pie
directions: Bake pie crust as directed.
Set aside to cool.

title: cucumber-blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine yogurt, Blue cheese, sugar, vinegar and pepper.
Stir in cucumber.
Cover and chill.
Stir in 1 to 2 tablespoons milk to thin, if desired.
Makes 1 1/2 cups (12 servings).

title: raspberry gelatin salad
directions: Combine ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour half of mixture in glass baking dish, approximately 8 x 12-inches.
Refrigerate until set.
Then add half the sour cream and top with remaining gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate until set, then top with remaining sour cream.
Chill.

title: reese's balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Add sugar until mixture can be formed into marble sized balls. Place in freezer.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with graham cracker crumbs and milk.
Add nuts.
Fold in egg whites. Bake in 2 waxed paper lined 8-inch layer cake pans in moderate oven (350°) for 25 minutes.

title: mock steak
directions: Mix hamburger, cracker crumbs, onion and 1/2 cup milk.
Pat evenly on cookie sheet and refrigerate overnight.
Cut in serving size pieces and dust with flour and brown.
Put in roasting pan with 1 can mushroom soup and rest of can of Pet milk.
Bake 1 hour 30 minutes at 325°.

title: marshmallow five layer bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix cake mix, margarine and water until blended.
Pat into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes.
Layer marshmallows, chips, coconut and pecans over crust.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes or until marshmallows begin to melt. Cool and cut into bars.

title: super spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
In medium bowl, stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Cut center out of 1 loaf of bread.
Put bowl of dip in center of bread.
Tear up other loaf into pieces used for dipping.
Makes 3 cups.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Combine ham, Ricotta cheese, salad dressing and onion; mix lightly.
Fill pasta shells with ham mixture.
Place, filled side up, in shallow baking dish.
Add 2 tablespoons cold water to dish. Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash dressing
directions: Can add a little poultry seasoning, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fudge cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add dry ingredients, then eggs, one at a time. Fold in pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Salt meat.
Roll in flour.
Brown entire surface in hot fat. Place on rack in Dutch oven.
Add 3 tablespoons flour to hot fat. Brown.
Add 3 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt and make a gravy, stirring while it cooks.
Place roast in Dutch oven.
Add gravy. Cover with tight fitting lid.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Add vegetables and cook about 20 minutes longer.
Roast may be cooked in pressure saucepan instead of Dutch oven.

title: tropical party punch
directions: Dissolve the Kool-Aid and sugar in water.
Add remaining ingredients just before serving.

title: candy apple pie
directions: In a large saucepan, combine 1 1/2 cups apple juice, candies, food coloring, vanilla and apples.
Bring to a boil, then simmer just until apples are tender, about 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, Dream Whip and cream cheese with beater.
Add sugar and cranberries and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; freeze.

title: prune cake or muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into loaf pan or muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes (loaf) or 15 to 20 minutes (muffins).
Serves 12.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat and onions in oil.
Add garlic salt, ginger and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add peppers and cover.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and soy sauce.
Add to ingredients.
Stir and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add 1 can Chinese vegetables, if desired.
Serve over rice.

title: roasted wild goose
directions: Soak goose in strong vinegar water for about 2 hours before cooking.
When ready to cook, rub goose well with salt and margarine.
Put onion, apple and celery inside goose and place in a roaster.
Cover and cook in oven at 325° until tender.
The age of the goose will determine the length of cooking time.
Remove goose to a serving platter.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine fruits; set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, beat pudding mix, milk and orange juice concentrate for 2 minutes.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Spoon over fruit; toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into two well-greased loaf pans.
Bake in a 300° oven for approximately 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: busy housewife banana pudding
directions: Make pudding as directed. Add condensed milk to pudding and whip until well mixed. Layer bananas, wafers and pudding. Top with Cool Whip and dessert is ready.

title: chili burgers
directions: Brown beef, stirring to separate.
Add soup and water.
Heat thoroughly, stirring now and then.
Serve on buns.
Top with cheese.

title: old fashioned sour cream drops
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Chill at least one hour.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook hamburger meat until done.
Add pasta sauce.
Let simmer for 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Cook lasagne noodles following directions on box.

title: cake mix zucchini bread
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, water, oil and cinnamon in large bowl. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in zucchini and orange peel.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Jab with toothpicks. Make syrup of sugar and orange juice.
Cook on medium until sugar dissolves.
Spoon over bread.
Cool and garnish with orange slices and confectioners sugar.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper, cooking 2 minutes. Slowly stir in milk and continually stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
In 2-quart casserole, arrange sliced potatoes, onion, then sauce.
Repeat layer.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake until potatoes are tender.
Makes for 10.

title: cantaloupe sorbet
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water (do not boil).
Bring to just under room temperature.
Add cantaloupe, cinnamon, salt and Port-wine. Blend and freeze for 45 minutes.
Remove from freezer.
Stir in cream and freeze 1 hour to 1-1/2 hours.
Spoon into small dessert bowls and garnish with mint leaves.
Makes six to eight servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Put egg noodles in a casserole dish.
Add ground beef and cream of mushroom soup.
Top with Tater Tots and grated cheese.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cut apples into small pieces.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and lemon juice; let mixture settle for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs, 1 cup sugar, oil, vanilla, baking powder and flour until moist.

title: southwestern rice
directions: Prepare rice to package directions.
In large skillet brown meat and onion; drain.
Stir in other ingredients except rice and cheese; heat through.
Remove from heat.
Add rice.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: cherry deluxe pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese together and layer on crust.
Add layer of crushed pecans, followed by layer of Cool Whip and top with cherry pie filling.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: nutritious pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt and oil.
Stir in flour.
Let rise for 5 minutes.
Add favorite toppings.
Bake for 20 minutes in a pizza pan at 425°.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Place all ingredients in large
bowl
and
mix
well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Touch tops in
sugar
and place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen, good cookies.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Mix salt and cabbage.
Let salt and cabbage stand 1 hour. Squeeze out excess moisture.
Add carrots and peppers.
While this is standing for 1 hour, make the dressing.

title: turkey a la king
directions: Empty can of soup into cooking container.
Measure milk into can until 2/3 full.
Blend a little milk at a time into the soup and stir until well blended.
In skillet cook onion in butter or margarine and also cook sweet pepper (red) until both are limp and onion is transparent.
Add to the soup mixture.
Add parsley and blend well.
At this point, either microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes until it comes to a boil, or cook over stove, stirring constantly until it comes to a boil.
Watch closely that it doesn't stick.
Add turkey and heat until warm approximately 3 minutes in microwave or stirring constantly on the stove.
Serve over toast or split biscuits.
tags: cream of chicken soup with mushrooms

title: easy hamburger and rice casserole
directions: In 10-inch skillet, brown hamburger.
Drain.
Add frozen vegetables, rice, soup, milk, onion and half the cheese.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
To serve, sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix all of these ingredients with stick of margarine on top. Cook in microwave Full power 2 1/2 minutes.
Put nuts in and stir until
margarine is mixed in well.
Pour in pan with wax paper. Chill for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix liquid ingredients separately and pour into dry.
Stir together well.
Pour into an 8 x 4-inch greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour. Doubled recipe makes 5 gift loaf pans.

title: ann's chex mix
directions: Melt oleo in very large
bowl.	Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Stir after
seconds.
Add
Worcestershire
sauce, garlic salt, onion salt, garlic powder, onion powder, cayenne, mixed nuts and cereal (Crispix or Chex).
Mix well.
Microwave on High 6 minutes, stirring after each minute.

title: fusilli tricolore with artichokes and sun dried tomatoes
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add hot pepper flakes, garlic, scallions, tomatoes and artichoke pieces and cook until scallions are softened and slightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Add cooked and drained Antoine's Fusilli and toss.
Season with salt and pepper and add Parmesan cheese to taste.
Toss well and serve with additional Parmesan.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: coconut surprise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour the bottom only of a 9x13x2 inch baking pan. Combine the cake mix, whole egg, egg whites, water and sour cream.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for about 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of cake.

title: buttermilk icing
directions: Mix together; keep stirring until it forms a ball when dropped in a bowl of water.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes. Cut cake into pieces.
Then pour icing on cake.

title: glorified hash
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Press into casserole dish.
Add Tater Tots by pushing them well into the mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: german pancakes
directions: In a blender, mix the eggs, flour and milk.
Preheat oven to 425°.
In a baking dish, melt a generous amount of butter.
Add the mixture from the blender and bake for 20 minutes.
Serve with lemon juice and maple syrup and dust with powdered sugar.
Enjoy!

title: easy wheat muffins
directions: Mix and bake in greased muffin tin at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Combine two tablespoons flour and salt in paper bag.
Add chicken pieces and shake to coat.
Brown chicken in hot butter, then remove to plate.
In same pan saute onion until tender.
Stir in remaining flour, paprika and white pepper.
Cook for one minute. Add broth and cook, stirring until thickened.
Return chicken to pan and simmer, covered, about 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken and arrange in baking dish.
Empty sour cream into medium bowl.
Gradually add hot paprika sauce, stirring constantly. Adjust seasonings.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Serve over hot noodles and garnish with parsley.
Makes four servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Blend in milk, flour and egg.
Add corn and salt to taste.
Cook in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Will be too dry if overcooked.

title: fast chicken and rice casserole
directions: *May use 2 cups chicken broth instead of water.

title: orange and carrot salad
directions: Blend soft drink mix into mayonnaise.
Combine carrots, pineapple chunks and mayonnaise.
Mix and chill before serving. Stir just before serving.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and shortening. Pour boiling water over mixture gradually. Add eggs and vinegar; mix well and cool in refrigerator. Roll out and put in pie pans. Makes 3 to 4 pie crusts.

title: frozen raspberry dessert
directions: Thaw frozen berries. Rinse carefully. Set aside some for garnish.
In a mixer, combine berries with 1/2 tablespoon sugar and liqueur.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.

Add remaining sugar and beat a few more seconds. Add raspberry mixture. Whip the cream. Carefully fold into raspberry-egg mixture. Spoon mixture into chocolate cups or small individual serving bowls. Freeze for 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peach kuchen(serves 1)
directions: Mix 1 1/4 cups flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Cut in butter (or margarine) until pieces are about the size of a pea. Stir in 2 tablespoons sour cream. Press mixture into a 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 375°. Spread peaches on baked crust. Mix remaining flour, salt, sour cream, egg yolks and sugar together. Pour over peaches. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Chill and serve with ice cream, whipped cream or plain.

title: round steak gravy
directions: Pound steak to tenderize and brown in skillet.
Put water, soup, milk and gravy mix in crock-pot.
Stir and put on high heat.

title: deer stew
directions: Pressure cook frozen deer for 30 minutes.
Remove deer roast from cooker and drain cooker.
Slice onions, potatoes and carrots with bell pepper.
Add cream of celery soup and water to the sliced deer roast in the cooker.
Pressure cook another 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cream cheese cherry o' pie
directions: When cream cheese is room temperature, beat until fluffy. Gradually add sweetened condensed milk; beat until well blended. Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before garnishing top of pie with cherry pie filling.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Microwave chicken on meat rack for 7 minutes per pound on Medium-high (70%).
Cut chicken into small pieces.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Dissolve baking soda in the buttermilk.
Cream butter; add sugar and then eggs.
Alternately add 1/2 the flour-salt mixture with the buttermilk.
Roll the nuts, candy and dates in the remaining flour.
Add these to the batter with the coconut.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: orange glazed cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the flour, sugar, soda, pumpkin pie spice, salt and baking powder.
In separate bowl, stir together remaining ingredients until well blended.
Combine with flour mixture.
Stir until well moistened.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until done. Cool completely.

title: french cream pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar
and flour together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat
and
add
milk,
coconut,
nuts and vanilla. Pour into a 9-inch
partially
baked
pie crust.
Bake at 325° until done (is
done when toothpick comes out clean), approximately 40 to 50 minutes.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Mix and chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine for 1/2 minute.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.

title: chicken and vegetable bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix all ingredients except 1/2 can of fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir.
Sprinkle with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and cut sweet potatoes into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook in lightly salted water to cover until tender.
Drain and mash with mixer until smooth and well blended.
Measure; should be about 3 cups.
Add sugar.
Mix well and add oleo.
Mix in well.

title: cauliflower
directions: Remove outer leaves and separate cauliflower into flowerets. Parboil in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Fry in oil until golden brown.

title: peanut butter apple dessert
directions: In a bowl, combine crumbs, brown sugar, 1/2 cup peanut butter, and butter; spoon half into a 3 qt. bowl.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth; fold in whipped topping.
Spread half over crumb mixture in the bowl.
Top with one can of pie filling.
Combine powdered sugar, cinnamon, and remaining peanut butter until crumbly; sprinkle half over pie filling.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: bumble berry pie
directions: Combine all frozen fruit in a bowl and thaw in refrigerator overnight.
Prepare double crust pie crust.
Spray and flour pie pan.
Line pie pan with crust.
Mix thawed fruit and other ingredients to bottom pie crust.
Seal top crust to pie.
Slit the top of pie crust and brush with milk.
Sprinkle granulated sugar on top.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes or until juice is bubbly.
Serve warm.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and stir well.
This may be used over pork ribs, beef or whatever.

title: baked chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Toss lightly and spoon into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Top with cheese and potato chips.
Return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes to melt cheese and brown chips.

title: gatah(armenian sweet bread)
directions: Mix first 4 dry ingredients.
Heat butter, Crisco and milk until warm and add to dry ingredients.
Blend 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add 1/2 cup flour or enough to make thick batter.
Add 4 eggs and beat 2 minutes longer.
Stir in 3 more cups flour and knead by hand a few minutes.
Let rise 2 hours.
Roll out about 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick; cut in 2-inch pieces and brush tops with yolk of egg and 3 drops of oil.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13 pan. Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream. Pour half of batter into prepared pan.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften the yeast in the water; set aside.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm.
In a mixing bowl, combine cottage cheese with sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt and soda.
Add the flour slowly, beating well after each addition.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size (50 to 60 minutes).
Stir dough down and turn into a well greased round 1 1/2 to 2 quart casserole dish.
Let rise in a warm place until light (30 to 40 minutes). Bake at 300° for 45 minutes until golden brown.
Brush with soft butter and sprinkle with garlic salt.

title: corn mazatlan
directions: Drain corn, reserving 2 tablespoons of liquid.
Combine reserved liquid and cream cheese in saucepan.
Heat and blend until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice with a fork or wire whisk.
Fold in Cool Whip and pineapple.
Pour mixture into pie crusts and refrigerate for a few hours until set.
Keep pie in refrigerator until all is eaten.
This recipe is from Billy's mother, Margaret Majors.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Combine ground beef, pepper and onion.
Cook until meat is browned. Drain. Stir in remaining ingredients. Spoon into a lightly greased baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: randi's chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In a large bowl, beat butter with sugar and brown sugar at medium speed until creamy and lightened in color (about 4 minutes). Add vanilla and egg, mix on low speed until incorporated. Stir in oats. Fold in chocolate chips. Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake 8 to 9 minutes for chewy cookies, 10 to 11 minutes for crisp cookies. Cool 1 minute on baking sheet; remove to wire cooking racks. Store in tightly covered container.

title: pluck-it-cake
directions: Cut biscuits (uncooked) into quarters.
Set aside.
Heat other ingredients until sugar melts and is slightly thickened.
Grease a Bundt cake pan with margarine and place half of biscuits in pan. Pour half of hot ingredients over biscuits.
Repeat and slightly shake pan to distribute hot mixture.
Bake at 300° for 55 minutes. Invert on plate and "pluck and eat."

title: easy as 1-2-3 lasagna
directions: Mix all ingredients together with ground beef.
Boil noodles. Drain.
Place a portion in bottom of buttered baking dish.
Spread part of your mixture on noodles.
Add cheese generously in between layers.
Repeat and repeat.
Bake for approximately 40 minutes at 400° or until cheese is melted thoroughly.
Great with bread sticks and a garden salad.
If you have any sauce leftover you can freeze for a later date.

title: no-bake pumpkin pie
directions: In heavy medium saucepan, combine unflavored gelatin, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in condensed milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Let stand 1 minute.
Over low heat, cook and stir constantly until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens slightly, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pumpkin and mix well.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours until set.

title: mom's apple pie(yield: one pie)
directions: 1. Place cut up apples in a medium-sized bowl.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Heat in microwave or in a 350° oven until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Roll meat in flour; brown in 4 tablespoons fat.
Cover with boiling water; simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, onions, potatoes, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaf, thyme and consomme beef soup.
Cook for 1 hour.
Add peas; cook for 15 minutes.
Thicken if necessary.

title: grandma pike's soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs in until blended.
Stir in flour alternately with sour milk.
(One cup of milk and 1 tablespoon of vinegar will make sour milk.)
Chill dough overnight or a few hours.
Roll out and cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Makes about 3 dozen soft cookies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Put in a casserole dish with soup.
Add cheese and butter; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
The last 3 to 5 minutes of baking time, add the crushed French onions, or you can omit the French fried onions and add crushed Ritz crackers with some butter on top.

title: porcupine meat balls(diabetic recipe)
directions: Mix in large pan the soup, water, onion and green pepper.
Add meat, rice and seasonings.
Shape into small balls; place into soup mixture.
Simmer slowly for 40 minutes.
Serve on warm plate with sauce spooned over meatballs.
When served, rice sticks out of meatballs, making them look like little porcupines.

title: beef roast with onion soup mix
directions: Mix soups together and put half of mixture in roasting pan. Place roast on mixture and cover roast with remainder of mixture. Add water to pan.
Place in oven at 250° for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Makes good gravy to serve over rice.

title: shrimp rice casserole
directions: Boil rice as directed. Melt butter.
Add soup, lemon juice, onion and pepper.
Stir until smooth. Add shrimp and parsley. Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Press 6 green pepper rings into top with butter pats.
Cover with cheese and bake.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add sugar to ground cranberries.
Let stand 2 hours.
Mix rest of the ingredients.
Add whipped cream to cranberries. Refrigerate.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, pudding, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip together in mixer.
Fold in bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: perfect fudge
directions: Put the sugar, evaporated milk and margarine in saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it comes to a full rolling boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add chocolate chips, nuts, marshmallows and vanilla; stir until well blended and marshmallows are melted completely.
Pour into a buttered dish and cool.
This recipe can be used also with peanut butter chips, excluding the nuts.
Makes 4 pounds.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie pan 2/3 full of peeled, sliced apples.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
In small bowl combine margarine, butter, 1 cup sugar, flour, egg and walnuts. Pour over apples.
Bake 45 minutes, or until top is browned in 350° oven.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pecans, eggs and butter.
Pat into shallow 9 x 13-inch pan that has been well-greased and floured.

title: broccoli & beef wellington squares
directions: Brown meat and drain well. Add all ingredients (except rolls); heat & simmer for 10 minutes. Separate dough; use 2 triangles for each square; seal (pinch together) diagonal perferations. Place mixture in center of square & bring edges together & press edges to seal. Place squares onto ungreased cookie sheet & bake at 375° for about 22 minutes (until golden brown). Wonderful entree for buffets.

title: spaghetti slaw
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Rinse in cold water.

title: fresh vegetable frittata
directions: Layer pepper, mushrooms and half of cheese in a lightly greased deep dish pie plate.
Top with asparagus and remaining cheese.
Combine eggs and remaining ingredients; pour evenly over cheese.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Partially thaw lemonade and mix with Eagle brand milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into piecrust.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
May substitute limeade.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, pineapple and sugar.
Add Cool Whip and fold.

title: cornflakes candy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in saucepan.
Cook 2 minutes, boiling slowly.
Add cornflakes and drop by the tablespoon on waxed paper.

title: cheese ball
directions: Leave all cheese out to get soft.
Mix all together.
Place in refrigerator until you can form a ball.
You can use butter on hands.
Roll in nuts.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Chill. Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Indent with thumb and fill with jelly.
Bake at 350° until jelly bubbles.

title: coconut pie
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients, except coconut.
Cover and blend for 10 seconds.
Scrape sides and blend another 10 seconds.
Add coconut and blend for 2 seconds.
Pour into greased 10 inch pie plate.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush the Oreo cookies.
Mix pudding, using 4 cups milk; set aside.
Mix powdered sugar, Cool Whip, cream cheese and margarine until creamy.
Mix with pudding in cake pan.
Layer cookies, then pudding, then top with the rest of the cookies.
Chill until firm or real cold.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil and sugar and pour over the vegetables.

title: anna's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time; add vanilla.
Alternate milk and flour (include when sifting baking powder and salt).
Cook in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: guilt free creamy chicken
directions: Wash and pat the chicken breast dry.
Place cut side down in a baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients and spread over chicken breasts.
Bake at 375° for 30 - 40 minutes or until breasts are done.
Do not overcook.
The sauce remaining can be used to dabble over chicken.
Reheats well.

title: chow chow
directions: Add vinegar, black pepper, sugar, and salt to green tomatoes, cabbage and the onions.
Tie up clove and allspice in cloth, drop in mixtures and add water if needed to cook for 1 hour or until tender.
Add hot pepper if wanted.
Can in jars.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Add boiling water to shortening and mix until shortening is soft.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Roll out pastry for desired use.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients, except 1 cup milk.
Stir well. Let come to a good boil, stirring constantly.
Add the other cup of milk slowly.
(Do not stop boil.)
Cook until it forms a soft ball.
(This takes a long time.)
Add pecan halves.
Pour into large, buttered pan and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: crunchy cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; let cool and add remaining ingredients.
Put in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan or your favorite mold sprayed with Pam.
Cover and chill until firm.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze in electric freezer.

title: teaser dip for chips
directions: Mix first four ingredients with enough mayonnaise to make mixture of dip consistency. Season to taste.
Put in serving bowl. Top with grated cheese.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into 9 x 11 x 2-inch pan (approximately).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan.
When thoroughly cooled, blend pudding mix with milk and beat in cream cheese.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding-cheese mixture.
Spread over cooled cake. Sprinkle with pineapple, pecans, coconut and cherries.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: cream cheese banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in bananas and eggs.
Stir in baking powder, soda and nuts; do not beat. Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cover with foil the last 15 minutes. Freezes well.
Makes one loaf.

title: microwave fudge sauce
directions: Microwave first three ingredients on High for 1 1/2 minutes until melted.
Add the last three ingredients.
Beat until smooth. Microwave 5 to 6 minutes on High until mixture boils, stirring every 3 minutes.
Must boil to thicken.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and set aside.
While macaroni is hot, add butter and sour cream.
Stir. In separate saucepan, melt evaporated milk and Velveeta cheese together.
Place cooked macaroni into greased 2-quart casserole. Pour cheese and milk mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Put back in hot oven until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: hearty beef stew(crock-pot)
directions: Trim all fat from meat.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Mix thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low 12 hours or high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: summer vegetarian chili
directions: Rinse dried beans in cold water, sorting through and discarding any broken beans or debris.
In large bowl, soak beans in about 2 quarts water for 4 hours; drain.
In Dutch oven, combine beans, bay leaf and fresh cold water to cover.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Partially cover and simmer until beans are soft and tender, about 1 1/2 hours (add salt, if desired, about halfway through cooking).
In Dutch oven, heat oil; add onion, garlic, bell pepper and zucchini.
Over medium-low heat, saute about 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, can of water and seasonings; cook, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes.
To Dutch oven, add 2 cups drained, cooked beans (store remaining 2 to 3 cups beans for future use in a soup, salad or casserole).
Add corn and lemon juice; cook 15 additional minutes.
Taste and adjust seasoning if needed.
Delicious served with warm tortillas or tortilla chips.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk and soda, then hot water and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured 8-inch cake pans at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: consomme madrilene
directions: In saucepan, heat consomme just to a boil.
Stir in sherry. Pour into soup bowls.
Peel and slice avocado.
Garnish with avocado slices.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Combine 2 sticks margarine, sugar, egg and milk in saucepan. Boil 1 minute over medium heat, stirring constantly. Add nuts, coconut and cracker crumbs to mixture. Mix well. Spread half over whole crackers, then layer more crackers and the remainder of mixture.

title: cinnamon squares
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Add flour and cinnamon, sifted together.
Press out on large greased cookie sheet.
Mark in squares.
Brush with unbeaten egg white.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, mustard and cayenne.
Mix egg yolks and milk; stir in flour mixture.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Then add apple cider vinegar and butter.
Mix into dressing and cool.
Makes one cup.

title: fondue
directions: Cube the bread and set aside, covered.
Melt cheeses in a double boiler on top of stove.
(A fondue pot may be used, but is not necessary.)
When the cheeses are melted, serve immediately with the bread cubes.
Fondue or regular forks are needed as each "eater" dips into the same pot.
You may have to reheat the cheeses, as they cool quickly.
Stirring will keep cheeses from sticking to the pan.

title: deer meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into loaf.
Put 1 slice of bacon on top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut crunches
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, Karo and honey (do not boil).
Add the peanut butter; stir until melted.
Add the Cocoa Puffs; stir until coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: white chicken chili
directions: Place chicken, beans, salsa, chicken broth, cumin and cheese in large skillet; heat on medium until cheese is melted. Add crushed tortilla chips as topping.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat shortening, peanut butter, 1/2 cup sugar and brown sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
In another bowl, stir together flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add to shortening mixture, blending thoroughly.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Precook the ribs in water and vinegar (small amount to soften meat).
Precook for 20 minutes.

title: oriental slaw
directions: Shred the cabbage finely and place in a large bowl.
Slice green onions finely and add to bowl.
Place canola oil in a frypan and heat on medium.
When hot, add noodles, mashed fine, sesame seeds and almonds.
Brown this mixture until a nice golden color; cool.

title: orange rice salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in boiling water; mix rest of ingredients in except cream.
When salad begins to set, then fold in whipping cream.

title: liver strips with mushrooms
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper. Dredge liver strips and brown lightly and quickly in hot oil. Remove liver strips.
Pour off drippings. Add celery, onion, garlic and marjoram to frying pan and stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes before adding bouillon.
Bring to a simmer and add mushrooms and liver strips to pan.
Cook, stirring, about 3 minutes.
Add parsley last.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In medium saucepan over medium-high heat, heat oil.
Add garlic and onion; cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring.
Add tomatoes with juice, chicken broth, carrots, celery, parsley, basil and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add lima beans and water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings with 90 calories and 3 grams fat.

title: broccoli casserole with water chestnuts
directions: Place 1/2 of broccoli in a 9-inch casserole dish.
Place 1/2 of onions and 1/2 of chestnuts on top of broccoli.
Add 1 layer of American cheese.
Repeat layers.
Spread soup over top.
Place bread crumbs on top (optional).
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water about 30 minutes or until tender; drain potatoes and mash.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients except paprika; beat just until combined.
Spoon mixture into lightly buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: *If using yellow cake mix with pudding already in the mix, omit instant pudding, use 3 eggs instead of 4 and 1/3 cup oil instead of 1/2.

title: chicken dijon with artichokes
directions: In large nonstick skillet sprayed with vegetable spray, saute chicken in liquid butter mix over low heat.
Remove from pan.
Add flour and stir over low heat until smooth.
Add more liquid butter mix, if dry.
Stir in broth and skim milk.
Add mustard.
Add artichoke hearts and simmer chicken in sauce for 30 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: brandy slush
directions: Dissolve sugar in the boiling water; cool.
Put the tea bags in the 2 cups hot water; leave bags in water until cool.
Mix the brandy, orange juice and lemonade.
Add tea and sugar; mix with juice and brandy.
Put in freezer containers and freeze.
Serve 2/3 Slush to 1/3 7-Up.

title: crisp sweet pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers crosswise.
Dissolve lime in water.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours and pour off.
Rinse thoroughly in fresh water.
Let stand in fresh water three hours.
Drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar and spices.
Add enough water to cover; let set overnight, then boil gently 30 to 40 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Add just enough bread crumbs so you can roll mixture into balls, then roll balls in regular bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour, then put under broiler for 10 minutes.
These freeze well.

title: shrimp and asparagus appetizer
directions: Partially cook asparagus in boiling water.
In hot, medium skillet, add soy sauce and cooked asparagus.
Cook until asparagus begins to soften, about 3 minutes.
Add cooked shrimp, ginger and garlic.
Stir constantly and heat long enough to heat shrimp through.
Salt and pepper.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and let set overnight.
Use with cauliflower, celery, carrots, cucumbers and bell peppers.

title: shrimp diablo
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, melt butter, then add the remaining ingredients.
Cook 5 or 6 minutes or until warmed through.

title: broccoli sweet 'n sour
directions: Fry bacon, drain and crumble.
Combine remaining ingredients, heat and pour over hot broccoli.
Add bacon bits.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone whole chicken.
Brown onions and green peppers.
Prepare noodles as directed on package.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350°.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt
the
chocolate with butter in the top of a double boiler over medium heat.
Remove from water and cool slightly. Combine the eggs, sugar, salt, corn syrup and rum in a mixing bowl
and beat
to
blend.
Beat
in the cooled chocolate and butter.
Place pecans
in the bottom of the pie shell and add the egg mixture. Bake in a preheated oven (350°) for 40 to 50 minutes.
The
top should be soft and the center not quite set when
the pie is shaken.
Serve with whipped cream that barely holds a soft peak. Serves 6 or 8.

title: bacon crisps
directions: Wrap each cracker with half strip of bacon.
Place on a cookie rack over a shallow drip pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, turning once, at 400°.
Serve hot.
Makes 24.

title: easy pie crust(this crust will not shrink or get soggy.)
directions: In a 9-inch pie pan, put flour, salt and sugar.
In a cup, mix oil and milk; pour over flour mixture.
Mix well with fork.
Press down into pan to form a crust with fingers.
Do not prick holes!

title: banana pudding
directions: Line bottom and sides of 13 x 9 dish with wafers, slice bananas on top of wafers. Mix pudding according to package, add cool whip and whisk until smooth. Pour over bananas and wafers. Chill until set.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Unroll the rolls on a large cookie sheet, pressing the seams together.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes (until browned).
Cool completely.

title: cherry crunch dessert(quick and delicious)
directions: Mix together until crumbly.
Place half the crumbs in bottom of well buttered pan, 6 x 10-inch.
Pat down firm.
Pour on cherries and cover with rest of the crumbs.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: jello icebox cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and next 3 ingredients.
Let stand until cool. Refrigerate until mixture starts to set.
Whip Milnot and fold into Jell-O mixture.
Line spring-form pan or angel food cake pan with vanilla wafers.
Alternate 3 layers of vanilla wafers with 3 layers of Jell-O.
Chill until firm.

title: hot spinach balls
directions: Turn thawed spinach into a sieve and press out as much of liquid as possible.
Combine spinach with remaining ingredients. Form into balls.
Can freeze.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add pizza sauce and oregano.
Pour in dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with crescent rolls.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions and peppers in 1 tablespoon butter.
Coat meat with flour; brown in remaining butter.
Add onions and peppers, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until tender.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: watermelon rind sweet pickles
directions: Peel the pink and green from rind of one watermelon.
Cut in squares and soak in weak alum water about 24 hours, changing water once.
Then put on to boil in enough clear water to cover and cook until tender.
When you can pierce them with a straw, drain well and make a syrup of one quart of the ingredients.
Let come to a boil.
Add rind and boil slowly for 10 minutes.
Put in jar and seal.

title: melting moments
directions: Cream butter with 5 1/2 tablespoons confectioners sugar and cornstarch.
Add flour and mix well.
Roll into small balls (size of a nickel).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Dot with icing made of 3/4 cup of confectioners sugar or roll in remaining confectioners sugar.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Place chicken on cutting board and pound lightly with cleaver or heavy knife until about 1/4-inch thick.
Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into egg mixture, then crumbs.
Heat oil until very hot in large frying pan.
Quickly brown chicken on both sides.
Remove to shallow baking dish.
Pour excess oil from frying pan.
Stir tomato sauce, basil and garlic powder into frying pan.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in butter or margarine.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Place Mozzarella cheese over chicken.
Bake until cheese is melted (approximately 10 minutes).

title: knick-knacks
directions: Mix the last 6 ingredients.
Melt and pour over the cereals, peanuts and pretzel sticks.
Mix well.
Put in large shallow pan and bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Goodies will keep a long time, if you can keep out!

title: apple bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter, then add sliced zucchini, potatoes, herbs and stock.
Cook on low boil until tender.
Put through blender to puree.
Add half and half.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve hot or cold with grated cheese on top.
Broccoli may be used instead of zucchini.

title: original chex party mix(microwave recipe)
directions: In a small microwave-safe bowl, melt margarine on High.
Add seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Pour cereals, nuts and pretzels into 2 gallon resealable plastic bag.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture.
Seal top of bag and shake until pieces are evenly coated.
Pour contents of bag into large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put a sieve over a bowl or measuring cup.
Empty 1 can of beans into sieve to drain.
Put beans in casserole dish.
Repeat with other can of beans.
Throw away liquid.
Pour soup over beans and add lemon juice.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle French fried onions over casserole and bake for another 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into a serving bowl. Chill before serving.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in cornstarch.
Add milk and stir until thickened.
Turn heat down and add cheese.
Stir until melted. Makes 1/2 cup of sauce.
Great over broccoli, cauliflower, etc.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Lightly spray casserole dish; place chicken breasts flat on bottom of dish (don't stack chicken).
Pour Ragu sauce over chicken; liberally sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and remove foil; very liberally sprinkle with mozzarella cheese. Return to oven for about 10 minutes to melt the cheese.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix wet ingredients, then add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes. Let cool on cookie sheet before moving to rack.
These freeze well.

title: salmon salad
directions: Mix rice, onions, celery and Italian dressing. Add salmon; toss gently to mix. Spoon onto lettuce lined platter; garnish with green pepper. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Mix spinach, soup and sour cream. Put in well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with bread crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cho-ffles
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Heat and grease waffle iron.
Place 1 teaspoon of dough on iron.
Bake about 1 to 2 minutes.
Regrease iron as needed.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Mix together the sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add the raspberries; mix together.
Pour into prepared pie crust; cover with top crust.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 40 minutes, or until brown.

title: old kentucky lemonade
directions: Wash mint and remove leaves.
Mix lemon juice, sugar and water; pour over mint leaves.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Mix together and place in an airtight container.
When serving, use 2 to 3 teaspoons of mixture to 1 cup of hot water.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken into cubes; dip in egg and roll in cornstarch. Fry chicken in 4 tablespoons oil.
Remove and set aside.

title: red punch
directions: Mix all together and chill until ready to serve.

title: *beef and onions in wine(chiumlec)
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons of butter and olive oil over medium heat in 3-quart pan. Add the onions, garlic and meat cubes.
Brown the meat on all sides.
Add tomato paste.
Mix for a few minutes, coating meat.
Add the wine and enough hot water to just barely cover meat cubes.
Add vinegar, bay leaf, cumin, cinnamon, salt and pepper. Stir to mix well.
Reduce heat to a simmer and cover the pan.
Let onions sit in very hot water for a few minutes and then slip the skins off. Boil peeled onions in salted water (1 teaspoon salt) for 3 minutes in a covered pot.
Discard the water. Rinse onions with cool water and drain well.
Will make them sweeter.
Place remaining butter into frying pan. Brown onions over medium heat.
Set them aside.

title: simple savories
directions: Put cheese, bacon and onions through food chopper using fine blade.
Stir in mustard and mayonnaise.
Spread on bread.
Toast under broiler until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: german chocolate cake(carol's birthday cake)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour or line pans with waxed paper (two 9-inch cake pans).
Break chocolate in small pieces, add 1/4 cup water in saucepan.
When melted and cooled, add flour, baking soda, salt, sugar and buttermilk.
Combine butter, sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Blend well.
Gradually add chocolate and dry ingredients alternating with 2/3 cup water.
Mix well.
Do not overbeat.
Beat egg whites until stiff, fold in mixture.
Pour into layer pans (9-inch) and bake 30 to 35 minutes; in 3 round pans (8-inch) bake 25 to 30 minutes; or in 9 x 13-inch pan bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown dish
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Garnish with paprika or parsley flakes.

title: frozen dessert salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
Let partially thaw before meal. Unused portions may be refrozen.

title: chicken broccoli orientale
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook chicken, half at a time, until browned.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp. Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: reeses peanut butter bars
directions: Put graham crackers in blender and blend to fine powder.
Put in bowl and mix together with peanut butter, butter and powdered sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate for 1/2 hour. Melt chocolate and pour over.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: english muffin loaves(makes 2)
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry mixture and beat well.
Stir in enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch bread pans that have been greased and sprinkled with corn meal.
Sprinkle top with corn meal.
Cover; let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.
To serve, slice and toast.
Keep refrigerated.
Can be frozen.

title: mounds cake
directions: Mix
cake
mix	and
eggs; add buttermilk.
Blend well. Add vanilla.
Makes
3	layers	or cook in sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 or 45 minutes or until done.

title: texas spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scald milk in a large saucepan.
When bubbles begin to form around the edge, whisk in the cornmeal, bit by bit.
Stir until mixture thickens, then continue cooking over very low heat for 5 minutes, stirring now and again to make sure it does not stick on the bottom.
Add salt, fat and sugar, and cook several minutes longer.
Remove from the heat and stir in chiles, cheese and egg yolks. Grease a souffle dish with bacon fat or butter and heat in the oven.
Whip whites stiff, but not dry, and fold into the cornmeal mixture.
Place in the hot dish and bake 45 minutes, or until puffed up and beginning to brown on top. Serve with butter.
Serves 6.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine the dates, raisins, butter, brown sugar, molasses and hot water; simmer gently for 3 minutes.
Cool in a mixing bowl. Beat the eggs in cooled mixture.
Add the fruits and peels and chopped nuts.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add this mixture gradually to the fruit mixture, beating well after each addition.
Pour into 9-inch tube pan lined with waxed paper.
Bake very slowly (275°) for 3 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Cut up into bite-size pieces.
Combine soups, tomatoes, onion, milk and chili powder.
In a large casserole dish, place crushed Doritos in bottom.
Spread chicken over Doritos.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and top with grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Mix with cream soup.
Place in casserole dish. Drain corn and layer on top.
Then add layer of Tater Tots.
Bake until brown.
Cheese
on top is optional.

title: banana freeze
directions: You will also need measuring cups and spoons, blender and tall glass.

title: tuna waldorf spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: non-butter crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together into mixing bowl.
Mix the oil with the cold milk, and pour all at once into the flour.
Stir lightly with a fork until blended, adding more liquid if necessary to make dough hold together.
Divide the dough into 2 portions. Refrigerate until ready to prepare pie.
Yields 1 (9-inch), 2 crust pie, 8 servings.

title: oatmeal chocolate chunk cookies(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut the chocolate into approximately 1/4 chunks.
Combine the flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Beat together the butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat in the egg.
Stir in the flour mixture.
Add the oats, dates and chocolate.
Drop the dough by level teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake until the edges brown, 6 to 8 minutes.
Let cookies cool 1 minute on baking sheets before removing to racks.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook until tender the squash and onion.
Drain and mash.
Mix all ingredients together and fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in buttered dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding pie
directions: Follow directions on large box of cook and serve Jello brand chocolate pudding.
While hot pour into 1 graham cracker crust. Let set for 4 hours.
Top with whipped topping, when totally cool. Garnish with chocolate shavings.

title: easy rice casserole
directions: Add all ingredients to casserole dish; bake at 325° for 45 minutes to bake.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all together in 2-quart dish.
Bake at 400° until brown on top, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the cake tests done.

title: deviled ham spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on sandwich bread.

title: sun city specials
directions: Brown sausage meat and ground beef.
Drain well. Add cheese and seasonings.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Spread on 2 loaves of bread and freeze on a cookie sheet.
Then store in plastic bags.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all together in order given, then beat while adding boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until center springs back.
Makes 3 dozen cupcakes or 3-layer cake.
Frost with favorite chocolate frosting.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: In a 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine soup, water, rice, mushrooms and 1/2 can onions.
Arrange chicken on rice mixture; sprinkle with paprika and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: burrito bake
directions: Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2 inch.
Mix Bisquick, water and beans.
Spread in pie plate.
Layer remaining ingredients on bean mixture.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Bring to rolling boil.
