Cool and fold in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: shelter harbor apple pie
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add sour cream, vanilla and rind.
Mix well.
Add apples to mixture.
Stir.
Set aside.

title: tortilla taco chip dip
directions: Cream together sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with taco seasoning.
Put chopped onions next, then lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: butterscotch nuts
directions: Mix pudding mix with both kinds of sugar, milk and margarine. Cook over low heat until soft ball (about 10 minutes).
Add nuts; remove from heat.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour out onto waxed paper to cool, then break into pieces.

title: railroad pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add tomato soup, chili powder, salt, pepper and corn. Heat for 10 minutes. Place in a sprayed casserole dish. Press down.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer 20 minutes over medium heat.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in 2 cups of boiling water until tender.
Brown veggie burger with salsa and onion; mix all ingredients together. Pour in casserole dish.
Dot with butter and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: junkyard salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order
given.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until set.

title: smoked turkey pizza
directions: Brush Bobolli with pesto.
Fold turkey slices in quarters and cover Bobolli with turkey.
Arrange zucchini, onion, mushrooms and cheese over the turkey.
Lightly salt and spray pizza pan with Pam or aerosol oil spray.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tex-mex layered dip(cold)
directions: In a large flat 2-quart casserole, spread refried beans.
Mix sour cream with taco mix.
Spread on top of beans.
Layer picante and other ingredients in order, ending with olives.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve chilled with Tostitos.
Serves 20 as an appetizer.

title: sue's brown sugar pound cake
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter, white sugar and brown sugar well. Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Add plain flour, salt, baking powder, milk, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300° or until cake tests done.
Cool well before frosting.

title: puffy french toast
directions: Mix together flour and dry ingredients.
Blend milk with egg. Add to flour mixture and beat until smooth.
(May refrigerate overnight.)
Dip bread into batter and fry to golden brown on both sides.
Yields 8 slices.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Place chicken in a glass or stainless steel dish.
Pour mixture over chicken and allow to marinate at least 2 hours in the refrigerator.
Pour off marinade and grill 8 to 10 minutes per side.

title: fudge
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes or until soft ball forms when you drop some fudge into cold water.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until it becomes somewhat stiff and then put into a greased pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Cook beef, onion and garlic until beef is browned; drain.
Stir in water taco sauce, chiles, 1/4 cup olives and seasoning mix.
Cook over low heat for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Brown meat; set aside.
Peel and cut up eggplant.
Cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Saute bell pepper, celery and onion. Drain eggplant.
Mix all with ground meat and rice.
Put in casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Add the eggs.
Add grated zucchini and mix well, making a batter.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients, spoon into pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Crimp edge to seal.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.

title: mamaw waldrips "jelly roll"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: bread
directions: Mix together well.
Put into well-greased loaf pan.
Soften butter; put on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken.
Strip off bone and place chicken pieces in broth.
In another pan, mix together the flour, salt, broth and Crisco.
Stir.
Roll out on floured board, into thin (like noodles) 2-inch strips.
Heat remaining broth to boiling.
Drop in dumplings.
Add 1/2 cup of milk; salt and pepper to taste.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Leave lid off to keep dumplings from becoming soggy.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook chicken in water.
Boil until done.
Pull chicken off the bone; tear the chicken up.
Place in cold saucepan.
Add peppers and onions; add soy sauce.
Cook until peppers and onions are done, usually about 20 to 25 minutes, over medium heat.
Goes good with rice.

title: salmon pate
directions: Drain and mash salmon.
Mix with softened cream cheese, onion, lemon juice, horseradish and liquid smoke.
Use plastic wrap to form into a log.
Cover with wrap and refrigerate for 12 hours, at least.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together the Crisco and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add alternately with the milk and flavorings.
Pour into a lightly greased and floured Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool for 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: blueberry oven pancakes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Beat first 5 ingredients with wire whisk until blended. Add blueberries.
Spread in pan.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cut into 12 pieces and serve immediately with your favorite toppings.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Combine jello and pineapple in heavy saucepan.
Heat over low heat until jello is dissolved.
Stir in cream cheese until it blends well.
Remove from heat; stir in cranberry sauce and nuts. Chill until mixture starts to thicken.
Blend in Milnot.
Pour into mold and chill thoroughly.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Make pudding as directed on box.
Add all the ingredients except Cool Whip and the cookies.
Mix well.
Mix the crumbled cookies and 1/2 tub of Cool Whip into pudding mixture.
Put the other half of the Cool Whip on top of pudding mixture and garnish the top of Cool Whip with the whole cookies.

title: minestrone
directions: Day before in bowl cover beans with cold water.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Next day drain.
Turn chicken broth into a 1 qt. measure.
Add water to make one quart.
Pour into 8-qt. kettle with 2 more quarts of water, 2 tsp. salt and the beans.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat, simmer, covered for 1 hour.
Meanwhile, wash cabbage and quarter and remove core with sharp knife.
Slice each quarter thinly.
Pare carrots, slice on diagonal, 1/4 inch thick. Pare potatoes, slice 1/2 inch thick, cut into 1/2 inch cubes.
Add to soup with canned tomatoes.
Cover, cook 1/2 hour longer. Meanwhile, peel onions, cut in half, slice thinly.
In 1/4 cup hot oil in medium skillet saute onions, stirring about 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Slice celery on diagonal, 1/8 inch thick.
Wash zucchini, slice into rounds, 1/4 inch thick.
Hold tomatoes on fork over heat, just to split skin, then peel with knife.
Slice 1/2 thick cut into 1/2 inch cubes.
Press 1 clove garlic.
Add vegetables to onion with 1/2 tsp. salt and the pepper.
Cook slowly, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes.
Add to bean mixture with 1/4 cup parsley and spaghetti.
Cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: potato cheese dish
directions: Mix together. Put half in pan and spread 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese. Repeat 2 cups cheese all together. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter and chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy. Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add egg whites, beating well.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Set aside.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, soup and cheese.
Layer with cabbage and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: wednesday night supper rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add shortening, sugar and salt to hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in eggs and yeast mixture.
Beat in flour.
Let rise 1 hour.
Roll out and let rise until ready to bake.

title: oyster stew
directions: Scald milk.
Heat oysters in their own juice for 5 minutes. Add butter, seasonings and hot milk to oysters.
Serve immediately.
Serves 2.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses get soft and beat all together.
Add chipped meat. Then shape into ball and put nuts on outside of cheese ball.

title: peaches and cream cheese pie
directions: In a medium size bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, salt, butter or margarine, milk, egg and pudding and beat 2 minutes. Pour into greased deep 9-inch pie plate.
Next, place the peaches on top of the batter.
Combine the cream cheese, sugar and reserved peach juice and beat 2 minutes.
Mix the 1 teaspoon sugar and the cinnamon together and sprinkle over top.
Bake 35 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Cool and chill.
Ready to serve.

title: steak and chicken fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken and steak in Italian dressing for 1 hour in refrigerator.

title: ham casserole
directions: In a buttered 9-inch baking dish, sprinkle 1/4-inch layer of cracker crumbs.
Follow with layers of ingredients as listed; repeat to fill dish, and top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes, or until bubbly and crusty.
Yields about 6 to 8 servings.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. In a medium bowl, beat eggs, cream, salt, and pepper. Crumble bacon onto chilled pie crust. Sprinkle shredded cheese over bacon. Pour cream mixture over cheese. Bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 300 degrees and bake for 40 minutes longer or until knife comes out clean.

title: delicate lemon pie
directions: Prepare pastry and make an unbaked 9 inch pastry shell. Chill while filling is being prepared.
Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time beating after each one.
Add flour, stir in milk, lemon rind, and juice.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff but not dry.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake on lower shelf in hot oven about 30 minutes at 425 degrees or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Grease and flour Bundt pan. Cook at 325° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven and cool.

title: lane's rice pudding
directions: Put all ingredients, except cream, into casserole dish.
Place in 375° oven.
Stir every 20 minutes for 1 1/2 hours.
Then put in cream and don't stir for 1/2 hour.

title: easy chicken corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, stir all ingredients until well blended. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Lower heat and simmer briefly. Makes four servings.

title: angel food cake delight
directions: Mix jello and when almost set add fruit cocktail, extra pieces of pineapple are good.
Whip Dream Whip, fold part of Dream Whip into jello and fruit leaving enough for top of cake.
Line baking dish with thin slices of angel food cake.
Spread jello mixture on cake, then another layer of cake.
Spread rest of Dream Whip on cake, spread with coconut.
Let set in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: barbecued salmon
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon of butter over low heat in a small, heavy saucepan.
Add the garlic and cook briefly.
Stir in wine and cook until reduced to 1/2 cup.
Add the remaining butter and stir until melted.
Stir in herbs and lemon rind.
Set aside.

title: cheesy broccoli, rice and chicken wrap
directions: Cook rice mixture as directed on package.

title: billie's tuna salad
directions: Use any size chunk tuna you want.
Add enough Kraft sandwich spread to make a good spread.
Any kind of pickle will do, just 1 or 2, cut up fine.
Add 2 or 3 cut up, boiled eggs.
Cut onions fine; add just a little bit.
Add some shredded lettuce.
Add the salt or a little cracker crumbs.
Ritz crackers are good. Remember to put crackers on last.

title: easy buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil and stir in jello until dissolved.
Add Cool Whip, buttermilk and pecans.
Mix together and chill.

title: chilli
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, salt and pepper in skillet; drain.
Combine ground beef with tomato sauce and tomatoes; cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add beans and chili powder.
Cook for 1/2 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Steam green beans and onion; add water chestnuts.
Make a cheese sauce.
Pour over beans (can use Cheez Whiz).
Add sliced almonds.

title: harvest or apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand for 1 hour.
Beat eggs; add oil, then the flour and dry ingredients.
Stir in apples.
Mix raisins and nuts with a little flour; add to apple mixture.
Blend well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with toasted slivered almonds.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Triscuits, crackers, French bread, etc.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. In a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Combine the two and bake in tube pan or two loaf pans at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: almond crust cherry cream pie
directions: Press almonds into pie shell.
Prick sides of crust only and bake as directed.
Cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Blend and let stand overnight.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix pecans, flour and margarine and spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours. Roll out dough and cut. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sliced apples in greased 8-inch square pan or baking dish.
Blend remaining ingredients until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar. Press in ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch, building up 1/2-inch edges.
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake until no indention remains when touched lightly in center, about 25 minutes.
Cool and cut.
Option:
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar before you cut.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until berries burst.
Fill individual serving dishes or place in a casserole dish.

title: marinated turkey breast
directions: Trim excess skin from turkey and place turkey in a large, resealable plastic bag.
In a bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Pour into bag with turkey.
Squeeze air from bag and seal.
Massage the bag to get the marinade all over the turkey.
Refrigerate for as little as 2 hours or as long as overnight.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine crumbs, oleo, peanut butter and sugar; work until smooth.
Press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over mixture.
Cut into squares when firm.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and eggs.
Slowly add to hot milk and cook until thick.
Cool pudding, then add half and half and vanilla.
Finish filling can with milk.
Freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: potato soup
directions: In a 3-quart pan, cook potatoes, onions, water and celery on medium 25 minutes or until tender.
Mix together sour cream, flour, salt and pepper.
Add sour cream mixture, milk, butter and bouillon cubes to soup.
Cook and stir 30 minutes.
Do not boil! Sprinkle with parsley.
Wonderful!!!!

title: simple baked beans
directions: Mix all the ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Lay bacon strips across top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken cashew
directions: Blend 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce; toss chicken and allow to marinate for 20 minutes.
In a large skillet, combine oil and garlic; add chicken.
Cook and stir several minutes.
Add vegetables and cashews; stir-fry until tender. Combine cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar, water and paprika.
Add to chicken mix and cook until thickened.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake
cake and make pudding according to package directions. Alternate
following
ingredients
and
put in a punch bowl:
cake (pinch
into small pieces), pudding, cake, cherry pie filling, cake and pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients except butter and mustard.
Cook over low heat until smooth and thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and mustard.
Stir until blended.
Use as dressing for potato salad.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: picnic baked beans
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in a Dutch oven with 2 quarts of water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes.
Remove from the heat and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain and rinse.
Return beans to Dutch oven with remaining water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 1 hour or until beans are tender.
Drain, reserving cooking liquid.

title: microwave pecan pralines
directions: In deep bowl, combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt. Microwave on 70% power for about 10 minutes, stirring and scraping the sides of the bowl several times.
Add butter and pecans and continue cooking at 70% power about 10 to 20 minutes until creamy and slightly thickened.
Quickly drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: hawaiian burgers(makes 14)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pineapple rings (but do not add the pineapple juice).
Cook on your grill.
Approximately 5 minutes before done, place the pineapple rings on each burger.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each.
Stir in vanilla.
Add vanilla wafers alternately with milk, 1/4 at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Spoon into a well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown and tests done. Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients (first five ingredients).
Add remaining ingredients, folding in nuts after the rest is well mixed.
Bake in floured/greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pan for at least 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients together in saucepan and heat until it begins to thicken.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake until chocolate is set and crust is browned.
Approximately 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with meringue.

title: humus
directions: Boil the garbanzo beans in a pot (water should cover the beans).
When the beans are cooked and soft, remove from the stove and let it cool down.
Grind the garbanzo beans in a blender with the water left after boiling; add lemon juice.
Add salt and 6 spoonfuls tahini.
Put in Pyrex.
Add red pepper, olive oil and parsley (chopped) on top.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Prepare favorite pastry for double crust pie.
To make filling, mix apples in dry ingredients.
Dot with margarine.
Make several slits in top crust.
Cover pie with pastry, seal and flute edge. Bake in a 425° oven for 50 minutes.

title: yam-apple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease large casserole.
Drain yams and pineapple.
Reserve juices.
Place 2 cups of this reserved juice, the sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Stir in cinnamon and salt.
Peel the apples.
Core and slice.
Slice the yams if they are whole.
Spread them in bottom of casserole. Spread apples over yams and then top with pineapple.
Pour the sauce over all.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: banana - topped cake
directions: Grease bottom only of round baking dish (8 or 9-inch size). Prepare cake mix for 1 layer as directed on package.
Pour batter into a baking dish; spread evenly.
Microwave on Roast or Level 7 (Bake), uncovered, for 6 to 7 minutes, turning dish one-half turn after 3 minutes.
Microwave until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: sage pot roast
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown roast on both sides in oil.
Season with sage, salt and pepper.
Add beef broth.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions.
Cover and bake 1 hour longer or until the meat is tender and vegetables are cooked.
Remove roast and vegetables to a serving platter and keep warm.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir into pan juices. Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Serve with the roast.
Yields 12 servings.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in pineapple; add flour gradually and stir in nutmeg.
After mixing well, add nuts.
Chill 1 hour or overnight.
Keep covered in refrigerator.
Drop by spoonfuls and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
You can keep these for 2 or 3 days and bake as you want.
This is a good cookie that isn't so sweet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo and cheese.
Add to broccoli.
Mix 1 stick oleo with cracker crumbs. Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan as follows: cracker crumbs, then broccoli mixture, cracker crumbs, etc.
Last layer should be cracker crumbs.
Glass baking dish is recommended.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: skiing at vail chicken dish
directions: Remove skin from breasts and place in bottom of baking dish. Spoon soup on breasts.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over and then place Swiss cheese pieces on chicken. Cover with foil and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil and continue to bake for about 20 minutes. Serve with white rice or baked herb rice (recipe included somewhere in this cookbook).

title: broccoli-cheese soup no. 1
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions.
Cool and blend in blender with part of milk until creamy.
Melt butter and add flour to make smooth paste.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Add broccoli; heat thoroughly.

title: orange syrup
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients; heat and stir.
Serve warm.

title: vanille kipterl(german christmas cookies)
directions: Put flour on board, in center of flour put sugar, vanilla and egg yolks.
Mix.
Put almonds and butter (cut in small pieces) on top.
Knead until dough is very smooth.
Let dough rest for 30 to 40 minutes.
Form little crescents out of dough.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
While still hot, roll in powdered sugar.

title: microwave poached eggs
directions: Grease poacher with oil, margarine or butter.
Add 1 teaspoon of water.
Place 1 egg in each holder.
Pierce white and yolk with toothpick.
Cover and cook 45 to 120 seconds.
Hold cover firmly and turn over.
Eggs will fall onto tray.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: *I like to mix flavorings.
I put 1/2 teaspoon lemon, 1/2 teaspoon orange, 1/2 teaspoon almond and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3 inch pan. In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat peanut butter and corn syrup until smooth. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time. Gradually beat in milk. Stir in flour mixture just until moistened. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan; cool on wire rack.

title: sri lankan style potatoes
directions: Boil, peel and cut potatoes into large chunks. Fry onions until golden brown.
Add rest of the ingredients and combine potatoes.
Stir for a few seconds.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies (place in Ziploc bag, roll with rolling pin).
Drizzle with butter.
Cover with ice cream.
Layer with fudge sauce.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into dish and layer carrots, celery, sliced onions and frozen peas.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise together. Spread on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet; add sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Roll biscuits and place in muffin pan with sides flowering over 1/4-inch.
Pour meat mixture 3/4 full.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Mix flour, nuts, salt, soda and sugar by hand.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans which are greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes and turn out on wire rack.

title: cheese blitzes
directions: Remove crusts from bread and roll flat with rolling pin.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Spread cream cheese mixture on each slice of bread and roll into jelly roll shape.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Dip each piece into melted butter.
Roll in a mixture of 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until toasted looking.
Good warm, cold or frozen.

title: bill's pork tenderloin
directions: Mix and pour over meat.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or more. Grill or you may cook in your oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: ravioli casserole
directions: Spread 1/2 cup of spaghetti sauce in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Layer 1/2 the ravioli, 1 1/4 cups of sauce, 1 cup cottage cheese and 2 cups Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Coat Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Add margarine, onion and garlic; saute until tender.
Stir in eggplant, zucchini, green pepper, tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium-high heat for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and stir in carrot.
Cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating between each addition.
Beat well.
Add bananas and nuts. Stir in flour and soda.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Wrap in foil; store in fridge overnight.

title: diabetic sugarless cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream the butter until it is light.
Blend in sifted flour and baking powder.
Add liquid sweetener.
Combine with vanilla and other liquid, milk, juice or coffee and mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle cinnamon over dough and knead until streaked.
Shape dough into balls 1/2 inch in diameter and arrange on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten balls with fork dipped in cold water.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 30 cookies, 30 calories each.

title: aunt emma's rice pudding
directions: Wash rice four times in cold water in medium size pan.
Cover slightly with water; steam with lid on until water is taken up, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Check frequently; when you tilt pan and no water is seen, take off stove.
Put rest of ingredients in a large baking dish (about 3 1/2 quarts).
Add rice.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Stir occasionally during first 1/2 hour.

title: ginger cheese ball
directions: Mix together with hands and roll in coconut. Refrigerate and serve with gingersnaps.

title: kiwi lime cooler
directions: In large pitcher, place limeade concentrate.
Slowly add carbonated beverage.
Add kiwi.
Serve over ice.
Serves 4.

title: beef-cream cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, dried beef (chopped fine) and garlic well.
Roll into round ball.
Mix pecans and parsley and then roll cheese ball into the mixture.
Great for a party.

title: stuffed pork chops(yum...yum)
directions: Melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and celery and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened (8 to 10 minutes).
Stir in sage and water.
Bring to boil and then add stuffing mix.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Use fork to fluff stuffing.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine 1/3 flour, yeast, sugar and salt in mixing bowl; stir. Combine all liquid and shortening in bowl; heat in microwave to 130°.
Combine liquid with flour; mix on medium speed on mixer for 3 minutes.
Install dough hooks.
Add remaining flour; knead for 7 to 10 minutes.
Rise for 30 minutes.
Punch back down; roll once and make into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hershey's red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
In a separate dish, blend cocoa and food coloring; add to sugar mixture.
Add flour, buttermilk and salt alternately.
Mix soda and vinegar in a cup and add to batter.
Mix thoroughly.

title: chinese chews
directions: Line an 11 x 7-inch pan with foil.
Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, then vanilla.
Fold in nuts and dates.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage done; drain and set aside.
Beat eggs and milk, salt and mustard.
Line a greased baking dish with a layer of bread.
Add sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over this. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fiesta cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour an 8 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Combine margarine in a large bowl and cream with sugar until light and creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each egg addition. Add chilli peppers (leave seeds in if you prefer a hotter taste). Add pimiento and cream-style corn and blend well. Then add the two cheeses and salt. In separate bowl, sift the flour, cornmeal and baking powder and add the cheese mixture. Blend and pour into the prepared baking dish. Reduce heat to 300° and bake 1 hour.

title: speckled trout for supper
directions: Wash trout and pat dry.
In a saucepan, melt butter in vermouth; stir in orange peel, lemon juice and vegetable seasoning.
Place trout in baking dish.
Brush each side of fish with butter mixture.
Lay potato slices on top of fish.
Sprinkle on garlic, onion and parsley.
Wrap baking dish in foil, sealing tightly.
Place sealed dish over barbecue coals and grill 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Or in the oven, bake covered at 325° until fish flakes easily.

title: potato cakes
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Drain off water.
Mash potatoes. Pour in milk.
Mix flour, seasoned salt, Italian seasoning and paprika, then add to milk and potatoes.
Take a spoon and spoon mixture into skillet.
Fry until brown on both sides.

title: chinese vegetable casserole
directions: Chop, prepare and measure ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°. Combine vegetables, onion, mayonnaise and soup into a large bowl. Using fingers, mix well.
Pour into a 1.5-quart casserole dish. Top with Cheddar cheese.
Set aside.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine apple cider and Hot Buttered Drink Mix in a mug and stir well.
Garnish with orange slice and sprinkle with nutmeg if desired.

title: cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.
You can substitute other flavors of Jell-O and fruit.

title: hot and spicy black-eyed peas
directions: Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and gradually add the sugar; cream together until light and fluffy. Add well beaten eggs. Sift flour before measuring and add to it the spices and the salt. Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add it and the flour mixture alternately to the sugar-butter-egg mixture, beating after each addition. Lightly dredge the nuts and fruit in a little extra flour to the mixture, then add the jam. Stir well. Grease and paper line two 9-inch cake pans 2-inches deep. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until done. Ice with caramel icing.

title: lite banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding together.
Let thicken.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip; mix together.
Spoon pudding in a big bowl.
Layer wafers and bananas.
Keep on layering until pudding mix is used up.
Sprinkle vanilla wafers on top.
Let set for 15 minutes on table top.
Then refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter and butter together.
Gradually add Karo. Sift flour, sugar and salt together and stir into butter mixture. Then add slightly beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in moderate oven (300° to 325°) until golden brown and just a little shaky in the middle.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except berries with mixer.
Then fold in berries.
Bake in tube pan for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour on 350 degrees.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in a casserole for about 1 hour at 350°.
Excellent.

title: zippy onion dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cover; chill 1 hour. Serve with sliced vegetables and crackers. Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: my grandmother's chilli
directions: Brown ground
beef
and
pork
with
the onions.
After browning meat put
in
boiler
with other ingredients and boil slow for 20 or 30 minutes; add 1 can red kidney beans.

title: liz's favorite pizza snacks(student favorite)
directions: In a frying pan, brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, oregano and garlic salt.
Pat each biscuit out to form its own crust.
Place crusts on a cookie sheet.
Top each crust with some of the ground beef mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: party sandwiches
directions: In saucepan, combine egg yolks, sugar and lemon juice with rind. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Remove from heat. Add cream cheese and beat until smooth. Stir in nuts. Spread mayonnaise on bread slices. Top bread with lemon mixture. Slice into pretty little sandwiches. Good finger food.

title: chess squares
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brownie mix; add egg and blend.
Pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese until fluffy.
Add 3 eggs and powdered sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over brownie mixture and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown.
Let cool and cut into squares and refrigerate.

title: corn, potato, ham chowder
directions: In a large pot, cook potato, carrots, celery and ham in water about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Drain and remove vegetables, reserving liquid.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk.
Stir in sugar to which 2 tablespoons of flour has been added.
Add melted oleo and coconut.
Bake in a 10-inch unbaked pie shell at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Very good!

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix egg and milk; add dry ingredients and cubed bread.
Make into 1 oblong dumpling about 8 inches long.
Let rise 1 hour under large mixing bowl.
Put into boiling water and boil for 10 minutes in covered kettle.
Turn and boil for another 10 minutes.
Cut with a knife or string.

title: delicious pork roast
directions: Sprinkle 1
teaspoon
Mrs. Dash in bottom of roast pan. Sprinkle roast
with Mrs.
Dash.
Place roast in pan.
Pour in water.
Cover with	foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until bones can be removed with kitchen tongs.
Eat and enjoy!

title: corn casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients together and bake at 325° until brown and set.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Combine yeast, whole wheat flour, 1 cup unbleached flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Heat honey, butter and milk until liquids are very warm.
Add gradually to flour mixture.
Mix on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Knead in 1/2 cup unbleached flour until dough forms a ball (about 5 to 7 minutes).
Cover and let rise 1 hour, until doubled.
Punch dough down; divide in half.
Form each half into 12 to 18 smooth balls, depending on how large you want the rolls to be.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: graham cracker date roll
directions: Roll crackers, place in bowl, reserving 1 cup.
Pit dates and cut fine.
Cut marshmallows if large. Combine date, nuts, and marshmallows with crackers in bowl.
Mix well with just enough cream to hold mixture together.
Form mixture into a roll, and roll in reserved crumbs to coat well.
Chill several hours, slice, and serve with whipped cream.

title: grilled cheese
directions: Put bread (one slice) and put cheese on bread.
Put other slice bread and put margarine on top.
Cut on high frypan.
Turn when brown and cheese has melted.
Let Mom clean up pan, but fix her one grilled cheese first.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Slice
onions.
Cook
in
shortening
with
ground beef until meat is brown.
Add cut celery, bouillon cube (dissolved in 1 cup boiling
water) and add flavoring to meat.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve over rice.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Slowly add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolk and flour.
Add vanilla and mix well. Chill dough at least one hour.
Place on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Gently press a cherry or pecan into each cookie.
Bake at 325° for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken, broth, carrot, celery, onion, thyme and salt in a large pot.
Bring to boil, then reduce to low heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from pan to cool.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut into small pieces.
Set aside.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook beans; drain and reserve liquid.
Combine onions, red pepper, soup and water in pan; heat through.
Blend sour cream and curry powder into soup mixture.
Stir in lima beans.
Turn mixture into a 6-cup casserole.
Combine bread crumbs with melted butter. Stir in bacon crumbles.
Sprinkle over lima bean mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice sugar cookies and put into greased cookie sheet.
Bake until brown at 350°.
Let cool.

title: cheese cake
directions: Butter a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Dust with crumbs.
Make thin layer of crumbs on bottom for crust.
Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Beat eggs, 2 at a time; mix into cheese mixture. Add flour, vanilla and cream; mix.
Pour over crumbs.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 65 minutes.
Shut off oven; leave in for 30 minutes.
Open oven door; leave in for 30 more minutes. Take out of oven; remove from pan.
Chill.
Top with fruit.

title: red and white salad
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x 13 pan. Chill until firm. Mix 1 package cherry jello and pour over salad. Chill until firm.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine dry ingredients. Beat butter and sugars until creamy. Add eggs one at a time and beat in well. Add vanilla. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Add chips and nuts. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls on ungreased baking sheets. Bake 9 to 11 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil in lightly salted water until tender.
Drain well.
Beat with electric mixer.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.	Put in a 9 inch x 13 inch pan.	Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until golden around the edges.

title: company green beans
directions: Cook green beans in boiling water until tender.
Drain water from beans.
Stir into beans 1 can Campbell's mushroom soup.
Pour mixture into serving dish.
Garnish with sliced almonds.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower and water in a 1 1/2-quart covered casserole.
Microwave 9 minutes on High; drain.
Combine mayo, onion, mustard and salt.
Spoon mustard sauce on top of cauliflower.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes. Let stand 2 minutes.
Serve.

title: two coconut pies
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into the unbaked pie crusts. Bake at 350° until good and brown.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread in a large bowl, add all ingredients and place in refrigerator.
Best if prepared the night before serving. (If prepared the night before, do not add tomato until ready to serve.)

title: easy oven stew
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a paper bag.
Drop portion of beef into bag.
Shake until coated.
Place in 8-quart casserole dish with oil.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes; stir well.

title: vicky's spinach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in well-oiled deep pie pan for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken-broccoli pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a glass pie dish.
Mix 1 cup cheese, chicken, partially cooked broccoli and spoon into pie pan. Beat eggs; add milk, then Bisquick.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in spices to taste.
Pour egg mixture into pie pan, covering chicken-broccoli mixture.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese is just melted.
Serve warm.

title: raisin cake
directions: Stew raisins in 2 cups water for 15 minutes; let cool.
Cream together melted butter, egg, oil, spices, sugar, flour, salt and cool water.
Add cooled raisins and baking soda mixture.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: amanda's favorite carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain water.
In small saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and ginger.
Add orange juice.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in butter or margarine.
Pour over hot carrots, stirring lightly to coat.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: texas hash
directions: Dice and cook onions in oil.
Add bell pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add ground beef; cook until beef is completely separated. Stir in tomatoes, uncooked rice, chili powder, salt and pepper. Pour in covered casserole dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°. Remove cover the last 15 minutes.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Put butter in while hot, then add soup and corn.
Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Add cheese the last few minutes.

title: classic walnut pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine eggs, sugar, flour, syrup, butter and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Arrange walnuts on top.
Bake in lower third of oven at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce oven to 350°.
Bake an additional 35 to 45 minutes or until center appears set.
Cool completely.

title: date delights
directions: Cook until thick the Eagle Brand milk, chopped dates and butter.
Add pecans.
Spread on Ritz crackers.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Mix any flavor jello with cottage cheese.
Mix fruits.
Add mixtures to Cool Whip.
Stir well.
Refrigerate.
(Add chopped nuts if desired.)

title: yesteryear pumpkin pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 2-quart casserole, crumble bread. Combine eggs, milk, pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla. Add raisins.
Stir into bread.
Set casserole in larger casserole or baking dish.
Fill larger dish with hot water.
Bake 70 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve warm or chilled with stirred cream.**

title: beef-mushroom stir-fry
directions: Trim
excess fat from meat.
Partially freeze meat; cut diagonally	across the grain into thin strips.
Combine water, soy sauce, cornstarch and bouillon granules; set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon Puritan oil in a large skillet or wok.
Stir-fry onions, pepper and	garlic	1
1/2 to 2 minutes on medium-high heat.
Remove
from
skillet.
Add	mushrooms, water chestnuts and snow peas;	stir-fry
to 4 minutes.
Remove vegetables. Add the remaining
tablespoon
Puritan oil to skillet.
Add beef; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Stir soy mixture; add to meat. Cook and stir
until
bubbly.
Return
vegetables
to skillet; toss to coat.
Cook,
covered,
for
1 minute, or until heated through. Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no-bake peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, milk and butter in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil, then cook for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop tablespoon size on wax paper and let cool.

title: marika and marc's aunt terri's chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Follow recipe on chocolate cake mix box.
Add the pudding and chips.
Bake as directed.

title: cheese soup
directions: Chop carrots and celery; cook in boiling water 10 minutes or until tender.
Chop onion and cook in butter until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add milk slowly, stirring until smooth.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add cheese, vegetables and cooking liquid.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Yields 6 servings.

title: san diego cocktail
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: eva's mean chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a skillet, heat Macayo's enchilada sauce.
In another skillet, stir in a cup of Macayo's enchilada sauce to shredded chicken until heated.
Put all chopped vegetables and olives on a large plate for easy access in preparing the enchiladas.

title: judy's tuna surprise
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as box directions says.
Add tuna, tomatoes, peas, can of cream of chicken soup, milk, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes, until brown on top.

title: turtles
directions: Mix the German chocolate cake mix with the oleo and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Spread 1/2 batter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Melt together the Kraft caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat or in microwave.
Spread over bottom layer.
Sprinkle the nuts and chocolate chips over the caramels.
Spread rest of cake batter over the top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir all together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven until firm or set.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mixes and prepare according to package directions, using 5 cups milk and a wire whisk.
Add sour cream and 1/3 of whipped topping to pudding; stir well.
Line a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with vanilla wafers; reserve remaining wafers.
Slice bananas over wafers.
Pour pudding mixture over bananas.
Line edge of dish with wafers, reserving 4 wafers to crumble and sprinkle on top.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding.
Cover and chill.
Sprinkle crumbled wafers over topping before serving.
Yields 15 servings.

title: german meat loaf
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together; then add 2 pounds of ground beef.
Mix them and form a loaf 10 inches long by 8 inches wide.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours. Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: chicken spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread on bread.
Makes 1 1/2 loaves.

title: grande potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until done.
Drain and let cool. Thinly slice unpeeled potatoes.
In skillet, melt butter and saute pepper and onion until tender.
Add soup, milk and 4 ounces of cheese and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in hot pepper sauce, green chilies and salt.
Add potatoes and toss gently.
Pour into buttered casserole and top with 1/4 cup grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: brownies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and chocolate syrup in a large bowl; mix well. Add eggs and flour; mix well. Add nuts and mix well. Place batter in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: fruit bowl
directions: Partially thaw frozen fruit.
Add bananas and sugar.
Mix together.

title: broccoli and cheese dish
directions: Saute onion, celery and cheese in 1 tablespoon butter.
Cook broccoli.
Add cooked rice.
Mix other ingredients and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 minutes at 475°.

title: tomato and prawns
directions: Saute onions in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, bay leaf, garlic, water and sugar.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add peeled shrimp and cook 5 minutes.
Place mixture in casserole and add crumbled Feta.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Place 4 uncooked noodles in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread half of beef mix over noodles.
Top with 4 more noodles and remaining mixture. Combine water and sauce; pour over all.
Cover tightly with foil. Heat at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (until noodles are tender).

title: carrot salad
directions: Shred carrots.
Add raisins and Miracle Whip.
Stir and/or mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: kahlua
directions: Put sugar, water and coffee in large pot and bring to a boil. Let simmer one hour.
Let cool to room temperature (do not force). Add remaining ingredients as you stir.
Pour into bottles.
Makes 2 1/2 fifths.

title: sausage-apple stacks
directions: Combine apples, onion and crumbs.
Make 8 sausage patties. Top 4 patties with stuffing, then a sausage patty.
Bake in a shallow pan in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Bring pineapple and syrup and sugar to a boil.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add cold water; let partially set.
Fold in grated mild cheese and Cool Whip.
Fold in pecans and mold.

title: moist bread stuffing
directions: In a 5 to 8 quart saucepan, cook onion and celery in butter over medium heat until tender, about 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; add bread and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Stuff 12 to 16 pound turkey or put stuffing in 9 x 13-inch pan covered with foil and bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Good for any bird.

title: tomatoes rockefeller
directions: Arrange tomato slices in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well to remove excess water.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Mound mixture on tomato slices.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until spinach mixture is set.
Yields 12 servings.

title: fall fruit salad
directions: Combine cranberries, marshmallows and sugar.
Chill overnight. Add rest of ingredients.
Serve soon after mixing.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon or ham; drain fat.
Mix with all other ingredients.
(Do not drain beans.)
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours covered, 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: dressing
directions: *Bring chicken broth to boil; pour over bread.

title: apple special
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together apples, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 1/2 tsp. cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.

title: peas and mushrooms in cream
directions: Drop peas into boiling water and let simmer about 5 minutes or until tender; drain.
Cut mushrooms into quarters.
Heat butter in a saucepan and add shallots.
Cook briefly, stirring.
Add mushrooms and cook, stirring about 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Add cream and cook, stirring about 1 minute.
Add peas; stir to blend.
Serve immediately.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Brown pork
chops
in a small amount of oil in skillet; drain. Cover
bottom
of 2 1/2 quart casserole with rice.
Top with pork chops.
Place
slice of onion on each pork chop. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb or peach crisp
directions: Boil fruit with sugar, cornstarch, water and add vanilla. Combine margarine, flour, brown sugar and oatmeal.
Put 2/3 of this mixture in loaf pan and press down.
Pour fruit over this and put remaining dry crumb mixture on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ed's bourbon balls
directions: Place chopped pecans in a glass bowl and cover with whiskey. Let stand overnight.
Melt butter and combine with confectioners sugar and pecan/bourbon mixture.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Let batter cool (1 hour to overnight).
Roll into balls.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour or in freezer for 30 minutes.
Melt the chocolate and keep it at minimum heat.
Using toothpicks, dip balls into chocolate and place onto wax paper.
Makes 90 to 160, depending on the size.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer chopped lettuce, celery, bell pepper, water chestnuts, onions and English peas.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise and spread over top.
Cover with cheese and bacon bits.
Chill overnight.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Turn on the oven to 400°.
Line twelve muffin pan cups with paper baking cups or grease well with shortening.
In a medium bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt with a wooden spoon.
Add fruit and stir until evenly mixed.

title: hot crabmeat dip appetizers
directions: Thoroughly blend all the ingredients together except the almonds and spoon into small casserole or ovenproof dish. Sprinkle with almonds and bake until bubbly.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into florets; wash and drain thoroughly.
Combine broccoli, cauliflower, celery, green onions and thawed, uncooked peas.
Combine salad dressing, sour cream, garlic salt, salt, sugar and pepper.
Pour dressing over vegetables and mix well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: sausage bread roll(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Prepare hot roll mix per directions on box.
Knead 5 minutes; let rise.
Knead again and let rise 30 minutes.
While bread is rising, brown sausage.
Grate the cheese.
Separate dough in half. Roll out 1/2; sprinkle with seasoning salt, then 1/2 sausage and 1/2 cheeses.
Roll like jelly roll.
Put on to greased baking sheet.
Repeat with other half.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Top with butter.
Can freeze.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion together.
Drain well.
Mix everything together, except 1 cup of cheese for top.
Spread evenly in baking dish.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Put crushed wafers in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan (reserve some for top).
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until smooth. Spread over crumbs.
Whip cream stiff.
Mix with drained pineapple. Spread over mixture and top with remaining crumbs.
Chill overnight.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix oats, chips, coconut and nuts together in bowl.
In a pan, combine milk, salt, sugar and butter and bring to a boil.
Pour over oat mixture; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: chicken breast medallions
directions: Flatten thin chicken breasts.
Slice thinly the carrot, bell pepper and onion.
In vinegar, dissolve the bouillon, chopped fine garlic, oregano and black pepper.
Divide this mix in half. Marinate chicken breasts with mix. Add to ground beef the spices, 1/2 of mix and egg.
Let sit for awhile.
Flatten chicken breasts on board.
Cover with layer of ground beef.
Add sliced onion, bell pepper and carrot. Roll. Cook in shallow pan with 1 1/2 cups water for 1 hour. Cool. Serve sliced, garnished with parsley.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all ingredients, except mix melted butter and bread crumbs together.
Distribute on top evenly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Knife should come out clean.

title: poppy seed casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook the ground turkey, onion and green pepper until meat is no longer pink.
Drain off liquid.
Stir in the tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles according to package directions.

In a small bowl, combine the cheese, yogurt and the poppy seed; toss the cheese mixture with the hot noodles. Layer 3/4 of the noodle mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon the meat mixture over the center of the noodles.
Layer remaining noodle mixture over meat.
Bake covered at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Place turkey in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix soup, sour cream and milk together and pour over turkey.
Saute onion and celery.
Add broth and mix with dressing and spread dressing over top and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fish supreme
directions: Place butter in shallow baking dish.
Put into 400° oven until butter is browned but not burned.
Place fillets in hot butter and return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Then turn fillets over and baste with butter and juice.
Sprinkle each fillet with lemon juice, Worcestershire, cheese, salt, pepper, onion powder and paprika.
Place in oven for about 5 to 6 minutes or until done. Place under broiler and broil quickly.
Baste fillets with sauce.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix.
Pour on top of crust.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: noodles
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients, then add flour. Roll to desired thickness on flat floured surface. Let dry at least one hour. Cut into strips. Keep in an airtight Ziploc bag.

title: goldie's noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles until tender-firm, drain thoroughly and add all other ingredients.
Mix
well.
Pour
into
a
greased
9 x 14-inch Pyrex baking
dish and bake uncovered at 350° for about 35 minutes until well browned.
Serve as a side dish.

title: skillet chicken stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a shallow bowl.
Coat chicken.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Brown chicken.
Add onion and celery and cook for 3 minutes.
Stir in potatoes and carrots.
Combine broth, thyme, ketchup and cornstarch.
Stir into skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add egg and water (enough water to make it smooth; not too dry or not too runny).
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: meatballs, potatoes and gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes and cornstarch.
Shape into balls; fry on all sides.
Drain.
Peel and quarter potatoes. Put potatoes and meatballs in a large pot; cover with water.
Boil for about 20 minutes, or until done.
Remove potatoes and meatballs from liquid.
Mix the cornstarch with a little water to form a paste.
Add paste to the boiling liquid, stirring constantly until thickened.
Return potatoes and meatballs to gravy.
Heat through.

title: tri-color tortellini salad
directions: Boil tortellini according to instructions on package.
While the tortellini are cooking, mix the oil, vinegar, garlic and mustard together well.
Strain tortellini and add the oil mixture and all other ingredients and toss.
Let set for 15 minutes before serving.
It may be refrigerated and served the following day.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Cook onion with a small amount of bacon grease in a skillet. Add okra, tomatoes and 1 can of water. Add salt, pepper and 2 teaspoons sugar. Cook on medium heat until it cooks down and thickens.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix cake mix and Jell-O together dry.
Add oil, milk and eggs, one at a time.
Use mixing directions on back of box.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before frosting.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Add 1 package Jell-O to 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Dissolve well.
Into a large glass bowl or mold, pour 3/4 cup of Jell-O. Chill 15 minutes or until slightly firm.
Add 3 tablespoons sour cream to remaining Jell-O.
Pour on top of jelled Jell-O.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla; add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir in rolled oats. You can add raisins, coconut or nuts.
Drop by teaspoon about 2 inches apart onto well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 14 dozen.

title: creeping crust cobbler
directions: Melt butter in deep dish.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder. Add milk and mix.
Spoon over melted butter.
Heat fruit with sugar and pour over dough.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Crust will be golden brown and will rise to the top.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add broken bread. Let absorb liquid. Pour in 9 X 12 inch buttered pan. Cut butter in pats. Place on top. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350 degrees until brown, about 1 hour.

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Beat egg, sugar and vanilla by hand until light and fluffy. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Blend or fold in with apples and nuts (by hand).
Pour into well buttered cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in your crock-pot.
Cook at 212° for 10 to 12 hours.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: grandma d'amato's cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter to make crust.
Press into a spring-form pan and set aside.
Cream cheese and sugar together.
Add ricotta cheese, sour cream, eggs, vanilla and flour.
Beat until smooth; it will look like a milkshake.

title: ham dip
directions: Hint:
Leave sour cream out for an hour to soften.
Makes mixing easier.

title: wiener casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Put mushroom soup in casserole and stir in 1/2 can milk.
Slice wieners in rounds and chop onion.
Add wieners, chopped onion and other ingredients to soup.
Stir and then mix spaghetti.
Put in casserole in a 350° oven and let cook 30 minutes.

title: ostakaka(swedish dessert)
directions: Warm milk in large pan on stove until is pretty warm, but not hot to touch.
Mix rennet tablet in small amount of water to dissolve; set aside.
Using some of milk, mix with flour (as for making gravy) until smooth.
Then pour into remaining milk, mix, then add rennet; mix well.
Let set for 45 minutes until feels solid, then stir.
Using small wire strainer, remove whey from curds.
Beat eggs, sugar and cream; add to curds.
Stir well. Bake in greased baking dish until brown and done at 400° first 15 minutes, then 375° until done.
Check by inserting knife and coming out clean.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together sugars and flour.
Beat in thoroughly eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Fold in nuts.
Pour in pastry lined pans.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: homemade potato chips
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a nonstick baking sheet.
Arrange the potato slices in 1 layer on the baking sheet and bake, turning occasionally, for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken breasts and rice
directions: Layer rice and chicken.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and cream of chicken soup.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Remove cover and brown a few minutes.

title: wedding balls
directions: Sift flour and sift again.
Add salt.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Mix with electric mixer and add flour and nuts.
Mix well and form into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and roll into powdered sugar.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter; add cheese, Tabasco sauce, flour, salt and Rice Krispies.
Form in small balls and flatten with a fork dipped in warm water.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and cook until light brown.

title: 6 in 1 casserole
directions: Place half of the hamburg in the bottom of a buttered casserole dish.
Follow with 1/2 cup of celery, then layer 1/2 cup onion, then 1/2 cup carrots, then 1 cup potatoes and sprinkle 3 tablespoons raw rice over mixture.
Add some butter, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Pour over 1 can tomato soup.
Bake 3 hours in slow oven (300°).

title: atlanta gas light small cherry cheese cakes
directions: Thoroughly combine cream cheese, sugar, eggs, salt and lemon juice.
Fill paper cups 3/4 full.
Place close together on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Chill.
(May be stored, covered, in refrigerator one week or frozen.)
To serve, top with cherry and small amount of pie filling.
Makes approximately 10 1/2 dozen.
Nice to serve at teas or receptions.

title: quiche
directions: In medium bowl, mix eggs and milk together.
Set aside.
Line bottom of pie shell with cheese, then sausage.
Pour egg mixture into pie shell; add seasonings.
Sprinkle parsley in the middle. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat and continue cooking at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool.

title: ham and cheese roll ups
directions: Spread cream cheese on ham slices.
Roll ham up; cut diagonally into 1-1/2 inch sections.
Secure with toothpicks.

title: potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, celery, onion, carrots, chicken broth, garlic, salt and red pepper.
Cover and cook until tender (20
minutes).
Add one cup cream; heat.
In medium bowl, blend dip and flour; stir in the remaining cup of cream gradually. Pour about 1/3 of the hot potato mixture into the dip mixture and return to saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: russian tea
directions: Add 2 to 3 teaspoons of above mixture to 1 cup hot water.
Can be used with cold water, also.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender; add mushroom soup and garlic cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Add chicken and can of mushrooms.
In 2-quart casserole, put cooked broccoli; pour chicken mixture over broccoli and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sour-cream banana coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly coat 12-cup Bundt pan with vegetable cooking spray. In a small bowl, combine chocolate chips, walnuts, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar. Set aside. In a large bowl with an electric mixer at medium-high speed, beat butter and remaining sugar until light and fluffy. Reduce speed to slow; add the rest of the cinnamon and the remaining ingredients. Beat 3 minutes or just until completely smooth. Sprinkle 1/3 of the chocolate-nut sugar on the inside of the pan. Drop in half of the batter in big spoonfuls. Sprinkle with another third of the chocolate-sugar mixture. Pour in other half of the batter. Sprinkle with remaining chocolate-nut sugar. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the middle comes out clean. Cool. Turn coffee cake out of pan and cool completely before cutting. Serve crusty side up.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice thin.
Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt; mix with apples.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Fill with apple mixture; dot with butter.
Adjust crust; sprinkle with sugar for sparkle.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 50 minutes or until done.

title: chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs well and add sugar, flour, and meal.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into umbaked pie shell and bake 30-40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: gorgonzola mousse with roasted red pepper sauce
directions: Beat together in a blender.
Bake mousse in miniature muffin tin about 10 minutes.
Wrap each mini mousse in phyllo dough. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: diabetic coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together except egg whites.
Cook until thick over medium heat.
Pour into crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add a pinch of salt, 1 tablespoon sugar and 3 packages Sweet 'N Low; beat until blended.
Top pie and brown slightly in 300° oven.

title: easy caramel corn
directions: Put butter, brown sugar, syrup and salt in microwave in casserole for 2 minutes at High power. Stir and microwave another 2 minutes.
Put popcorn in brown bag.
Pour syrup mixture over popcorn and shake.
Put in microwave on High for 1 minute. Shake again.
Microwave another 1 minute.
Shake and microwave 1 more minute.
Put on cookie sheet to dry. Enjoy.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: Mix all together.
Wash and dry fish.
Heat oil 1 to 2 inches deep.
Dip fish in batter and fry.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and add chicken.
Dice other ingredients and add to cheese mixture.
Spread on flour tortillas. Roll and chill.
Slice and serve with picante sauce.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix butter or margarine (melted) together with flour.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then cool.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Stir in milk.
Sift and add flour, salt and baking powder. Blend in blueberries.
Pour into greased tube pan and top with crumb mixture.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together until the butter is crumbly with cake mix and 1 egg.
Press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cream until fluffy: cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Pour over crumb crust. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes until golden brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cuban sandwich
directions: Split bread lengthwise.
Butter one side.
Spread mustard on other side.
Put a layer of ham, then roast pork, then salami and Swiss cheese.
Put dill pickle slices on top.
Cut sandwich into 4 servings and warm.

title: crescents
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla, then flour and nuts.
Shape into crescents and bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Makes 100 large or 150 small crescents.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: In mixing bowl, mix flour and eggs together, then add cream cheese, sweet butter and vanilla; stir well.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
With electric mixer at medium speed thoroughly mix shortening with sugar, then with eggs until very light and fluffy, about 4 minutes.
Then at low speed or blend beat in flour mixture alternately with bananas, just until smooth. Turn into pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove.
(Cool overnight before slicing.)

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add all other ingredients, except bread crumbs. Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and top with bread crumbs. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to

title: milk madness
directions: Pour cold milk into shaker or mixer.
Sprinkle gelatin over milk.
Put lid on shaker or mixer very tightly.
Shake or mix very hard for at least 1 minute.
(If using shaker, be sure to hold top and bottom of container.)
Pour into glass and drink right away.

title: orange liqueur
directions: Pare very thinly the rind from the orange (no whites).
Blot peel on paper towels to remove excess oil.
Put peel into a 4-cup screwtop jar.
Add 2 cups vodka.
Cap jar and store in a cool dark place for 2 days until the vodka has absorbed the flavor and color of the peel.
Remove peel and discard it.
Add sugar and shake vigorously until sugar is dissolved.
Add remaining cup of vodka and stir well.
Cap and store in a cool dark place for a week to age.
Makes 1 quart.

title: strawberry-melon slaw
directions: Toss the cabbage slaw and fruits in a large bowl.
Set aside. Stir Miracle Whip salad dressing, honey and poppy seeds in a small bowl.
Pour over the cabbage and fruits.
Gently mix together.
Refrigerate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves(golabk)
directions: Boil whole head of cabbage for about 5 to 10 minutes until leaves are a little limp.
Remove and cool.
Cut or pull off leaves and chop up remaining cabbage and set aside.
Try to keep each leaf in one piece.
Mix ingredients well and place small amount into each leaf and roll up securely.
Set aside until all are wrapped.
Place rest of cabbage in kettle and put cabbage rolls on top.
Add 1 quart tomatoes and 1/2 cup water.
Boil on stove about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Also can be baked at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: crab meat quiche
directions: Mix flour and milk.
Add eggs and mayonnaise.
Add cheese, crab meat, green onion, bacon bits and shrimp.
Pour into unbaked pie shell, then bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
(Makes 2 store bought 9-inch pie shells.)

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix grated cheese thoroughly with butter.
Sift flour, salt and cayenne pepper.
Add gradually to mixture.
Roll out and cut with small cutter.
Bake in 325° or 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: karen's cobbler
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together then blend in the milk.
Mix well.

title: microwave tea ring
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Place margarine in a round cake dish and microwave for 1 minute and 30 seconds on High or until margarine is melted.
Immediately stir brown sugar and cinnamon into melted margarine.
Add biscuit quarters, 1/4 at a time, and stir to coat with mixture.
Arrange biscuit quarters evenly in dish.
Microwave 4 to 5 minutes on High or until biscuits are slightly firm to touch.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; pack lightly into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
I like to bake mine in muffin pans.
Bake until light brown.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Heat broth, water, carrots, celery, onion and seasonings to boiling in Dutch oven.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer until carrots are tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in chicken and noodles.
Heat to boiling; reduce.
Simmer uncovered 7 to 10 minutes.
Stir in onions.
Yields 6 servings.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper. Cook until done. Drain, then put into casserole dish.
Heat soup and water.
Pour over mixture.
Put Tater Tots on top and cover with grated cheese. Cover with foil and cook 50 minutes at 350°.

title: date bars
directions: Boil sugar, milk and dates until a soft ball forms in cold water.
Remove from stove. Cool to lukewarm. Add vanilla, butter and nuts.
Beat until firm enough to form in a roll about 1 or 2-inches in diameter.
Roll closely in a clean wet cloth.
Let remain until cold. Remove from cloth.
Cut with sharp knife into slices 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.

title: pizza rolls
directions: Brown sausage and drain off grease.
Cut up Velveeta into small cubes.
Allow cheese to melt almost completely over sausage on low heat.
Add Ragu sauce and stir easy to mix.
Place small amount on each slice of bread and put on cookie sheet.
Place cookie sheet in freezer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove and place in storage container.
When needed, bake on cookie sheet, greased with Pam, at 350° for 10 plus minutes.
Remove and serve.

title: sweet and simple coleslaw
directions: Layer onion rings and green pepper rings over cabbage in large bowl.
Combine other 7 ingredients and heat to boiling.
Stir occasionally.
Pour over cabbage, onion and pepper.
Refrigerate, tightly covered, at least 4 hours.
Toss lightly.

title: hot cheddar stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash, pat dry and remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems and set aside.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Brush mushroom caps with butter and place in a shallow baking dish.
To remaining butter add onions and stems; saute 2 minutes.
Add bread crumbs, cheese, nuts, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir lightly.
Spoon into mushroom caps, piling high.

title: total chicken
directions: Place cereal and seasonings in blender until crushed to coarse texture, not powder. Pour into bowl. Beat egg and milk together in separate bowl. Dip chicken, one piece at a time, in egg mixture until covered, then dip in cereal mixture until coated. Place pieces side by side in large oven pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: bierocks
directions: Let dough raise according to recipe.
Shortly before dough is ready to use, brown hamburger and onion.
Add chopped cabbage and small amount of water.
Cover and steam until cabbage is tender. Let cool.

title: homemade (low-fat) ice cream
directions: Mix together.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Fill to full line with skim milk.
Freeze and enjoy.

title: noodle soup(sopa de fideos)
directions: Fry noodles in oil until lightly brown and remove from pan. Add tomato sauce and onion juice until it evaporates.
Add noodles, broth, parsley and season with salt and pepper.
Boil in low heat until noodles are cooked.
Serve in individual bowls and garnish with cheese.

title: rita's spaghetti and lasagna sauce
directions: For Spaghetti:
Brown meat; remove fat.
Boil water for 6 servings of noodles.
To meat, add sauce and spices; simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Good with garlic bread.

title: hawaiian fruit smoothie
directions: Mix in blender and serve.

title: potato pizza bake
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together.
Mix all other ingredients together. Pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 375° for one hour and 15 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: sugar-free reduced-fat pie pastry
directions: Combine flour, Equal and salt in medium bowl.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender until it resembles coarse crumbs. Mix in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing lightly with a fork until dough is formed.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Double recipe for a two-crust pie.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all together.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 275°, then 50 minutes at 300° or until top is golden brown.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in soup, sauce and milk.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes. In small skillet, dip tortillas in a little cooking oil until limp; drain.
Place the cheese on tortillas and roll up.
Place in skillet and cover.
Cook until heated through, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle with additional cheese; cover and cook until cheese melts.
This recipe will serve 6 people.

title: oven-barbecued pork tenderloin
directions: Place tenderloin in a large bowl with marinade.
Cover and chill eight hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Lift meat from marinade and roast.
Baste with marinade every fifteen minutes.

title: chicken and zucchini stew
directions: Drain the liquid from the tomatoes into a saucepan. Chop the tomatoes and set aside. Add the broth, green pepper and garlic to the tomato liquid. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium and cook for 10 minutes. Add reserved tomatoes, zucchini, pepper, salt and basil. Simmer until zucchini is tender, about 10 minutes. Reduce heat to low and add the chicken. Cook for 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings. Serving size 3 to 4 ounces chicken.

title: deep dish streusel apple pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl; toss to mix.
Spoon into a 6 x 10-inch casserole.
Combine 2 cups flour, brown sugar, salt and remaining 1 teaspoon pie spice in a bowl; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: jade empress chicken
directions: Skin and bone chicken.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Saute mushrooms in oil in skillet.
Toss lightly until mushrooms are light golden.
Stir in celery and peppers; cook 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in chicken, cooking until it turns creamy white.

title: double chocolate dips
directions: In a heavy small saucepan heat 2 squares chocolate over low heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool. In a large mixer bowl beat butter or margarine until softened. Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add milk, vanilla and cooled, melted chocolate. Beat well.
Add flour and beat until well mixed.
Using about 1 tablespoon of dough for each cookie shape into a 2 x 1/2-inch log.
Curve slightly to form a crescent shape. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven about 18 minutes or until done.
Remove and cool.

title: crisp squash-and-pepper toss
directions: Combine basil, oregano, thyme, salt, pepper, vinegar and water in a shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole; add squash.
