Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap; microwave at High for 3 to 4 minutes. Let stand, covered, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add onion, garlic, sweet red pepper and olive oil; toss gently.
Cover and microwave at High for 2 to 4 minutes.
Add sausage; toss gently.
Cover and microwave at High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: polish cabbage(from overrock inn)
directions: Cook cabbage until nearly done.
Combine with tomatoes and cook together.
Fry salt pork until crisp.
Add flour and cook until smooth.
Add to cabbage and cook together until smooth, adding seasonings until thick.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: brown rice
directions: Put in 3-quart Pyrex dish. Stir and cover. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Brown beef in oil in deep kettle.
Bring to boil rest of ingredients.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Thicken with flour and water to make gravy.
Serve over noodles.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Spray vegetable spray on Bundt cake pan.
Combine cake mix, sugar and vegetable oil.
Add next four ingredients and beat in mixer for 6 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed.
Pour in Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack and cool for 10 minutes.

title: potato chip munchies
directions: Mix margarine until softened.
Add sugar and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Gradually add flour and chips.
Beat until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Cool and munch away!
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk in large mixer bowl.
Beat until blended.
Add salt and vanilla, then sugar gradually while beating, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Yields enough for sides and tops of 2 layers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Make a
hole in the center,
pour all other ingredients in the
hole.
Beat
well. Pour into 3 or 4 greased and floured loaf
pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You may line your pans with wax
paper to be sure they won't stick.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Mix sour cream, ranch dressing and Miracle Whip.
Pour over vegetables and stir well.

title: baked eggplant appetizer
directions: Halve eggplant lengthwise.
Brush all sides with olive oil. Place halves, cut side down, on a baking sheet.
Bake 25 minutes. Brush onion, garlic and red pepper with oil and add to eggplant. Bake 25 to 30 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In medium bowl, beat yogurt, maple syrup, poppy seeds and salt until smooth.
Transfer to pitcher to serve immediately or pour into jar.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: curried fruit
directions: Combine butter, sugar and curry powder; bring to a boil. Drain the fruit.
Bake in a 325° oven until it bubbles.
Serve hot.
(Very good with ham.)

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add drained fruit and pecans. Refrigerate overnight.

title: hamburger raisin stuff
directions: Brown hamburg along with onion, green pepper and raisins.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: 2 cheese balls
directions: With a fork, mix together 3 cheeses and add remaining ingredients, except pecans and parsley.
Form into 2 balls.
Place pecans and parsley on 2 pieces of waxed paper and roll balls in mix until thoroughly covered.

title: very low-fat bran muffin
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Add egg substitute, buttermilk, oil, applesauce and cinnamon.
Stir to moisten. Cover and refrigerate until ready for use.
Bake in (sprayed) muffin tins at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Mixture will keep up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: triple dutch fudge bars
directions: Cook pudding as directed on package.
Blend in cake mix.
Pour in bar pan.
Sprinkle with chips and walnuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve hot water and Jell-O.
Mix in Jell-O the strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of Jell-O in dish; let congeal.
Leave other 1/2 of Jell-O out of refrigerator. When congealed, spread sour cream over.
Pour other half of Jell-O mixture over sour cream.
Put in refrigerator until jelled.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and cool.
Add vegetables, eggs, mayonnaise and corned beef.
Pour into loaf pan or mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Slice to serve.

title: maria's quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour into pie plate and bake at 400 degrees for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with Romano cheese.

title: sweet-sour apple beets
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together beets, apples, onions, salt and nutmeg.
If apples are very tart, add 1 tablespoon sugar. If they are bland, add 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Layer in greased casserole.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake for about 1 hour.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with onion.
Place Doritos in a casserole. Put pieces
of	boiled chicken next.
Mix soups with 1 cup of chicken broth and jalapeno pepper (chopped fine).
Heat, then pour over chicken.
Cover with grated cheese.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 5 o'clock rolls
directions: At 5:00 P. M. dissolve yeast in water in a large Tupperware bowl.
Add melted butter, salt, eggs and sugar.
Add flour to make a soft sticky dough.
Let stand in warm place.
Punch down several times each hour until 10:00 P.
M. (for a total of 5 hours).
Roll out dough 1/2 at a time.

title: chicken polynesian
directions: Place chicken breasts or thighs in pan.
Mix onion soup mix, preserves and French dressing well and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 10 more minutes.
Serve with a pot of rice and use sweet and sour gravy over rice and chicken.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave (30 seconds).
Mix cream cheese, tablespoon of milk and sugar until smooth.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture on bottom of crust.
Mix milk and pudding until smooth; should be thick.
Blend in pumpkin and spices. Spread mixture on top of cheese layer.
Chill for 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip when served.
Garnish with nuts if desired.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Boil water; add
jello.
Add petite marshmallows to hot mixture and let melt.
Add lemonade, mayonnaise, sugar, pecans and drained fruit.
Pour into a 2 quart Pyrex dish to congeal. After mixture has congealed, cover with topping.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Beat thoroughly.
Add grated squash and mix well.
Heat shortening.
Drop by tablespoon into hot shortening.
Brown on both sides.
Serve hot.

title: chile salsa
directions: Put all ingredients in a food processor.
Blend by pushing `Touch' button ON and OFF; approximately 10 -15 times, depending on how chunky you want it.
That's ALL there is to it!! Sometimes, I like this salsa blended with some sour cream.
It makes a delicious dip; also - "Blend in a little bit of Jesus Love!"

title: cranberry fudge
directions: Combine the sugar, margarine, cranberries and cream in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to medium. Cook for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in the vanilla chips and continue cooking until chips melt which should take about 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallow cream and pecans.
Pour into a well buttered 8 or 9 inch square pan.
Cool at room temperature.
It is best to keep this fudge in the refrigerator.
If you want a richer pink color, add a little red food coloring.

title: fruit punch(for 50 people)
directions: Rinse cans out with just a little water and add to juices. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
At the time of serving, divide the juice in half.
Add 2 quarts of ginger ale to 1/2 of the juice.
Just before serving, add half the sherbet.
Pour over crushed ice.
Do the remainder the same way at each addition to punch bowl.

title: cheese ball or dip
directions: Mix well all ingredients except nuts.
Form ball or loaf on small plate or platter; then cover with wax paper.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll in nuts or pat them on sides and top of loaf. Chill again.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: marbled double chocolate cheesecake squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 8 or 9-inch square baking pan with foil, extending edges over sides of pan.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Sift together.
Store in airtight container.
For 1 cup hot chocolate, add 1/4 cup of mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Heat in a deep skillet the oil, salt and pepper. Add cabbage, celery, bean sprouts, water chestnuts and sugar. Stir in broth and cook about 10 minutes.

title: betty's lemon squares
directions: 1. Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl, then cut in the butter until the mixture is crumbly.
Gather the particles and with lightly floured finger tips, press evenly and firmly over the bottom and 3/4 inch up the sides of a 9 x 9 x 2 baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350 degree oven until golden about 20 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and sugar.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Combine the two mixtures.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pork roast fajitas
directions: Cook roast until it falls apart.
Cool.
While cooling, slice peppers, onions and cheese cubes.
Trim away fat from roast and strip into small strips.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add peppers, onions and roast.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add cheese cubes.
Stir until cheese has melted.
Fill each tortilla with pork mixture. Top with tomatoes.
Fold.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Spray baking dish evenly with oil.
Cut beef into tiny pieces and line baking dish with it.
Place chicken on top of beef. Mix sour cream, soup, and spices.
Mix well, and pour over chicken breasts.
Cover and bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Serve gravy over cooked rice as a side dish.

title: steamed graham pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Have water boiling in canner.
Steam for 2 hours.
Serve hot with milk and sugar.
Serves 10 to 14.

title: porru salda(leek soup)
directions: In a large pot, bring to boil 3 to 4 quarts water.
Add leeks, potatoes and 2 tablespoons oil/fat.
When vegetables are cooked, add the garlic which has been fried in 2 tablespoons oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: apple pie
directions: Line plate with rich pastry.
Pare, core and cut apples.
Fill pie plate.
Mix the dry ingredients and lemon juice and sprinkle over the apples.
Dot over with butter.
Wet edges of under crust. Cover with upper crust, pressing the edges close together.
Pinch into a fluted rim.
Bake in a hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes, then in moderate oven (350°) for 40 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Pour 2 cups sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add 6 eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add Duncan Hines cake mix.
Then add 2 cups plain flour with soda and sour cream.

title: spicy beef pita sandwiches
directions: Cut beef into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Combine dressing, green onion and mustard in medium size bowl.
Add roast beef and peppers; mix well.
Cover; chill several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Immediately before serving, drain beef mixture, reserving dressing.
Add cheese to drained beef mixture, tossing lightly.
Combine mayonnaise with reserved dressing; mix well.
Open pita bread halves; line with lettuce and tomato.
Fill with beef and cheese mixture.
Top each with mayonnaise mixture and sprouts, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Makes 12 sandwich halves.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Make into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook meat, tomato sauce and diced onion until meat is done. Mix cheeses in a separate dish.
Add sour cream.
Cook noodles; drain and divide in half.
Line the bottom of dish with margarine and noodles.
Add all cheese mixture to the center of the noodles. Add remainder of the noodles on the top of the cheeses.
Pour meat mixture over top of the noodles.
Season to taste.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Saute garlic and scallops in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add shrimp and crab meat.
Stir.
Remove from heat.
Cook noodles.

title: pepper jelly(canning)
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in a blender and blend well together. Add 2 cups sugar. Blend well. Pour into saucepan. Stir in 4 more cups of sugar. Bring to a boil. Strain mixture and return to pan. Stir in the fruit pectin and food coloring. Return to full rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly. Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Skim off foam. Fill jars. Process 5 minutes in hot water bath. Delicious served with crackers and cream cheese.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 3 hours or until it sets.
Top with strawberries and desired amount of glaze. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat margarine in saucepan; add onion and green pepper.
Cook and stir over high heat until light brown.
Add tomatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil gently.
Cover tightly; lower heat and simmer gently 30 minutes.
If desired, you may add hamburger and bacon bits before cooking.

title: mile-high apple pie
directions: Roll 1/2 pastry on floured surface into circle 1 inch larger than inverted pie pan. Ease pastry into pan. Combine cornstarch, Equal measure, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; sprinkle over apples in large bowl and toss. Arrange apples in pie crust. Roll remaining pastry into circle large enough to fit top of pie. Cut hearts in pastry with cutters; place pastry on pie, seal edges, trim and flute.
Press pastry hearts on pastry. Bake in preheated 425° oven until pastry is golden and apples are tender, 40 to 50 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Roll the sugar if it is lumpy.
Mix the melted butter thoroughly with sugar; add beaten egg.
Sift dry ingredients and combine the 2 mixtures.
Make into roll.
Let stand 10 minutes. Then cut into slices and place on greased baking tin in moderate oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheesy rotini
directions: Prepare rotini as directed on package.
Drain.
In a large skillet, cook ground beef, green pepper and onion, over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes, bouillon, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in milk, Ricotta cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and rotini.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2-quart casserole with Pam.
In 3-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients except broccoli and salt.
Cook over medium heat and stir until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli.
Put in casserole and bake 30 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken in water with salt, pepper, garlic salt and 2 chicken bouillon cubes for 45 minutes.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Cook rice as directed and spread over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook broccoli and spread it over the rice.
Add a layer of chicken.
Mix mayonnaise, oil, cream of chicken soup and onion rings together and pour over chicken.
Cover with cheese and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add next 6 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes. Spoon into bowls and top with tortilla chips and cheese.

title: no fat vegetable dip
directions: Cook asparagus in microwave oven with garlic salt until soft. Drain.
Add Miracle Whip and horseradish.
(One crushed garlic clove may be used to replace the horseradish.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well.
Reserve some cracker crumbs to sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet onion relish
directions: Mix onion and pepper, sprinkle with salt and let stand 30 minutes.
Squeeze out juice by twisting in cheesecloth bag.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag.
Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and cook until thick, stirring often.
Put in jars and seal.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath. Serve with pork or even good on a hot dog.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Take a couple things of dough.
Take 10 chips in dough.
Take dough and put it on the foil.
Put it in the oven for 10 minutes at 8° Fahrenheit.
Take them out and cool.
Then eat.

title: deluxe pound cake
directions: Add flour and milk alternately (1/3 flour, 1/2 milk and 1/3 flour).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: special roast
directions: Mix
flour, salt, pepper and allspice together and coat the meat
with	this
mix.
Brown
the	meat
in
the oil in a 12-inch Dutch
oven.
Mix the catsup, garlic powder, vinegar, mushrooms, onions, sugar and bay leaves together and pour over meat.
Bake for 2 hours.

title: danish cheese surprises
directions: Spread 1 package crescent rolls on bottom of pan.
Beat sugar and vanilla into cream cheese until soft; spread on dough.
Place other package of dough on top; brush with egg.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Very good and easy.

title: hostess potatoes
directions: Mix and bake all but last 2 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove and top with crushed corn flakes and melted butter.
Mix and spread on top, return to oven and bake 15 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: two layer jello salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in drained pineapple juice and 1 1/2 cups water.
Heat to boiling.
Add the marshmallows; stir until dissolved.
Set aside until cool.
When cool, add drained pineapple and whipped topping.
Put in medium Pyrex flat dish. Refrigerate.
When set, pour cooled red jello over top.

title: pancho villa's layer cake
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Serve with chips.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Let cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter soften; blend together. Stir in flour. Chill for 1 hour. Shape in 2 dozen 1-inch balls. Place in ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin pans.
Press dough against bottom and sides.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to firm ball at 240° with candy thermometer. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Pour about 1/2 of sugar mixture over egg whites, beating constantly.
Cook remaining syrup to soft crack, 270°.
Add syrup slowly to first mixture, beating constantly until mixture holds its shape.
Add vanilla and nuts. Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: sue's banana pudding
directions: Mix the 3 cups milk and instant pudding.
Add sweetened milk; mix in.
Add Cool Whip; mix by hand well.
Place small amount in bottom of large bowl.
Top with wafers and bananas.
Layer as you wish, ending with wafers and bananas on top.
Makes plenty.

title: deep-fry batter fish and onion rings
directions: Mix together.
Add enough water so batter is a little thinner than pancake batter.

title: thousand island dressing(from brennan's in new orleans)
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly with whisk. Cover and chill before serving. Will keep about 1 week in the refrigerator.
Serve over lump crabmeat or romaine lettuce.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in eggs and oil, then add all other ingredients.
Stir until mixed well.
Do not beat.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool in pan.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Stuff slices of Jack cheese into split and seeded chilies in bottom of baking dish.
Mix together eggs, milk, flour and seasonings.
Pour grated Cheddar on top.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 40.

title: potatoes and hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and seasonings; drain.
Blend soups, milk and cheese.
Place 1/2 of sliced potatoes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Put 1/2 hamburger mixture, then 1/2 soup mixture.
Repeat layers. Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour in covered dish.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more or until potatoes are tender.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Roll the meat in flour and brown in butter; place in casserole. Add mushrooms and liquid, soup mix and water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Before serving, stir in sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: ethel's peppy green beans
directions: Cook bacon and remove from grease.
Add onion and tomato; cook slightly.
Add green beans, black pepper and crumbled bacon. Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: cranberry salad(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Peel oranges; put peeling and cranberries through food grinder. Remove white membrane from oranges and section them, breaking each section into three or four pieces.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: mrs. dull's barbecue sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pot or Dutch oven.
Stir together and cook over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Pour into sterile bottles or jars.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Saute chicken breasts in margarine in skillet for 20 minutes. Remove to warm platter; keep warm. Stir flour into pan drippings. Add broth and half and half.
Simmer until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add mustard; mix well.
Return chicken breasts to skillet.
Heat, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: Mix together the cracker crumbs, melted margarine and the sugar.
Press into a greased 9 x 13 pan (glass preferred) as a crust.
Cream together powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Prepare the Dream Whip and add to cream cheese mixture.
Blend thoroughly. Spoon mixture on crust.
Top with your choice of fruit.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; put into a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: portuguese omelet
directions: Mix all together; cook in skillet with 1 tablespoon oil.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook
noodles; mix all together.
Put sliced almonds on last 20 minutes of baking time.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: school day cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add last 4 ingredients. Spoon them out on wax paper to cool.

title: lynn's pasta suprise
directions: Boil pasta according to directions (no more than 8 minutes). Add mayo, mustard and milk mixed together.
Drain pasta and add liquid to it.
Should be enough to moisten all pasta but not runny.
Add more mayo if needed.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Garnish with fresh parsley and small pieces of tomato.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir flour into melted butter until it is smooth and free of any lumps.
Add remaining ingredients one by one except for the nutmeg.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle the top with nutmeg.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: apple stack cake
directions: Cream
shortening,
then add sugar, a little at a time, blending well.
Add molasses and mix well.	Add eggs, one at a time,
beating after each addition.
Add milk alternately with the sifted
dry
ingredients.	Beat well after each addition. Place mixture in six 9-inch greased and floured pans.
Spread until about 3/8 inch deep.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes. Cool and stack with applesauce.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Soak
beans overnight in water; drain.
Stir-fry onion, garlic and
salt pork in oil in a large, heavy kettle, 5 to 8 minutes over
moderate heat, until onion is pale golden.
Add beans
and broth.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add all remaining ingredients, except zucchini, parsley, macaroni and Parmesan. Cover
and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add 1 tablespoon
parsley, zucchini
and
macaroni.
Cover and simmer an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Taste and add additional seasonings,
if
needed.
Stir Parmesan into soup or sprinkle on top before serving.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until tender; drain and add green peppers.
Set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over carrots and pepper.
Let stand until cool.
Refrigerate until ready to use. May be kept several weeks.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine first 5 ingredients. Put in a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and bread. Drizzle with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through. Makes 4 servings.

title: baptist cakes
directions: Combine butter, sugar and salt in a large bowl. Add the milk and water. When lukewarm, add the dissolved yeast cake and 1/2 flour. Mix thoroughly with a spoon, then add another cup of flour. Continue to mix, adding balance of flour gradually. Turn out on a floured board and knead until smooth and elastic. Return to clean bowl. Cover with cloth and let rise until double in bulk. Turn out on board and roll to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut in strips of 2 1/2-inch wide and cut again to make squares or diamonds. Cover and let stand for 10 to 15 minutes. Fry in deep hot fat about 4 minutes or until a delicate brown. Serve with maple syrup or Milk Sauce. Serve hot.

title: corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups. Blend all ingredients about 20 seconds.
Beat 1 minute.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes; immediately remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: elegant crabmeat balls
directions: Drain and flake crabmeat.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into walnut-size balls.
Roll in corn meal.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 500° for a few minutes until brown.
Watch closely.
Serve with horseradish or cocktail sauce.

title: blue ribbon banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add mashed bananas, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder together and beat for 2 minutes.
Add coconut and pour into prepared pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 3 cheese lasagna
directions: Put noodles on to boil.
Fry hamburger meat; drain grease from pan.
Then add tomato paste, oregano, celery salt and onion to hamburger meat.
Let simmer.
When noodles are done, layer noodles, sauce and cheese in greased deep dish 9-inch pan, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni for 6 minutes; drain.
In medium saucepan, combine cornstarch, salt, dry mustard and pepper; stir in milk until smooth.
Add margarine.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium high heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Reserve 1/4 cup cheese for topping.
Stir in remaining cheese until melted.
Add sugar if used.
Add elbow macaroni.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake uncovered in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Makes 6 servings.

title: 5 can casserole
directions: Combine ingredients. Save some noodles to sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine in processor and blend until smooth and creamy.

title: chicken or turkey divan
directions: Cook broccoli several minutes; drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased casserole.
Layer chicken on top.
Combine soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs in butter.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry glaze
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar.
Add water.
Cook until it starts to boil.
Let simmer 10 minutes.
Add jello.
Chill.
Add to strawberries.

title: divinity candy
directions: Bring sugar, water and salt to rolling boil and boil only 2 minutes.
Place marshmallow cream in large bowl.
Pour hot syrup all at once onto marshmallow cream.
Stir until candy loses its gloss.
Add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Never fails!

title: chicken-cheddar tostados
directions: Combine chicken, taco seasoning, water and chilies.
Cook over low heat until liquid is reduced, about 5 minutes.
Set aside.

title: pear relish
directions: Boil zucchini in small amount of water for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and pineapple.
Boil 10 minutes more.
Remove from heat and measure fruit and liquid.
Add enough water to equal measure for 2 cookings of Sure-Jell.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In medium saucepan, cook onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons broth 5 to 7 minutes or until softened.
Add tomato sauce, honey, oregano, basil and white pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer gently for 20 minutes.
In a skillet or wok, combine red pepper, mushrooms, squash, carrots, broccoli and 2 tablespoons each balsamic vinegar and broth.
Stir-fry over high heat until crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.
Add peas and cook for 2 more minutes.
Set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon balsamic vinegar to sauce and cook for 5 minutes.
Reserve 1 cup sauce to serve at table. Pour remaining sauce over cooked pasta and toss thoroughly.
Add stir-fried vegetables and toss again.
Sprinkle green onion and parsley over top.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 13 dish with slices of cake. Sprinkle over top of cake, pineapple. Mix large box of Jello mix with 3 cups skim milk and pour over cake. Thinly slice 1 banana and place on top of pudding. Cover with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring the sugar, cocoa, butter and milk to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon out onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: marlene's baked lasagna
directions: Brown onions, green peppers and ground beef.
Add sauce, tomatoes, seasoning (4).
Cook noodles covered 14 minutes with 1 tablespoon salt.
Drain.
Spray pan with Pam or use shortening. Cover bottom of pan with a small amount of sauce.
Add 1/2 noodles, sauce, 3 cheeses; repeat layers of noodles, sauce and cheeses. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bologna candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk in 2-quart saucepan. Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage (234°), stirring occasionally. Add dates and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is very thick and leaves the side of the pan when stirred. Remove from heat. Stir in coconut and nuts.
Cool slightly. Turn out on wet towel.
Place in refrigerator and chill.
Make a roll 2-inches in diameter and about 18-inches long, like rolls of cookie dough. Cut in slices to serve.
Makes 2 1/4 pounds.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have all ingredients about 70°.
Sift before measuring.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Peel, core and thinly slice apples.
Place in dish; drizzle with honey.
Add cider.
Mix sugar, flour and spices in small bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples. Cover casserole with aluminum foil.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Pound out chicken with meat tenderizer.
Dip chicken breasts.

title: seafood dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Blend all ingredients except paprika. Spread mixture in a 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes until lightly browned.

title: glazed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pork chops in shallow Pyrex baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place 1 tablespoon margarine on each pork chop.
Spread 1 tablespoon sugar over each chop.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: brunch treat
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in pie pan in oven.
Remove.
Mix flour and milk.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Pour mixture over butter in pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Mixture will bake into a shell.
Cool slightly.
Fill with Cool Whip and fresh berries.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put in a baking pan (9 x 13-inch, quart-size) the French cut green beans, milk, mushroom soup, salt and pepper. Mix together. Then on top put fried onion rings.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: cherry magic
directions: Drain cherries, pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Save the cherry juice.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Add milk, flour, baking powder and salt. Pour over cherries.
Then sprinkle this mixture over the top:
sugar, cornstarch, and salt.
Take cherry juice you saved, and measure one cup (if not enough, add water to make one cup).
Put in pan, bring to boil.
Pour this over the top and bake one hour at 375°.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Combine pudding and pineapple first; add remaining ingredients.

title: tupperware hot chocolate mix
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Stir in milk powder and marshmallows. Store in airtight container. Use 3 to 4 tablespoons of mix to make 1 cup of cocoa.
Keeps up to 6 months.

title: chicken or ham casserole
directions: Mix uncooked Creamettes with soup and milk and refrigerate overnight.
Cook and bone chicken; cut in pieces (or 2 to 3 cups ham).
Sprinkle top with 1/2 pound Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan 1 hour at 350°.
It will solidify if let stand 5 minutes before cutting in squares.

title: ramp pickles
directions: Combine squash, ramps, cukes, peppers and cauliflower. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt and let stand in ice water 2 hours.

title: my father's tomato catsup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until it gets thick like catsup.
When thick, put in hot sterilized pint jars and seal. Process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes.

title: rosemary roast chicken
directions: The evening before, wash and dry the chicken.
Very carefully, stick your fingers between the skin and the meat of the breast. Turn the chicken over and do the same to as much of the back, thighs and legs as you can without tearing the skin.
Strip the rosemary leaves from the stems.
Finely chop rosemary leaves with the garlic and salt.
Push the mixture under the skin and spread it around.
Pepper the inside of the chicken.
Wrap it in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, unwrap and roast at 350° for 75 minutes or until done.

title: judy's relish "1984"
directions: Grind vegetables, using coarse blade.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt; let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine sugar, seasonings, vinegar and water; pour over vegetable mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot sterilized jars. Makes 8 pints.

title: praline's
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in large kettle on medium flame. Stir constantly. Boil 5 minutes. Add butter and chopped
nuts. Cook (boil 5 minutes). Test to soft ball. Let stand 5 minutes. Beat until it pulls away from side. Put teaspoonful on wax paper. Can wrap in Saran Wrap.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add pineapple and pecans to oleo and sugar; mix well.
Lay 6 graham crackers on foil.
Put mixture on crackers "thick."
Add 6 more crackers, then mixture; do this 4 or 5 more times.
Then use the rest of mixture to ice the top and sides.
Wrap the foil around the cake.
Freeze for 48 hours before using.
Slice as needed.
Put back in freezer.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: mock chop suey
directions: Brown beef and put in baking dish.
Saute onions and celery. Add rice and soups; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Crumble shrimp.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Serve with crackers.

title: potato supreme
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Brown beef in skillet.
Mix onion into beef and cook until done.
Mix potatoes into beef and onion until potatoes are done.
Pour ingredients into baking dish. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Heat in 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Boil chicken. In a skillet, saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Stir in chicken broth, brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce. Stir in 2 tablespoons of cornstarch for thickening.
Stir and cook until thick.
Then stir in chicken.
Serve with hot rice.

title: crackling bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients, then add the milk and cracklings. Form into small long rolls on a baking sheet and bake 20 minutes in oven until brown.

title: mom's corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Try stewed tomatoes instead of corn for a tasty alternative.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix, chill and serve.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Saute for about 5 minutes in oil the cabbage, onion, pepper and celery.
After sauteing for 5 minutes, add tomatoes, sugar and salt and pepper.
Cover and cook slowly for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: never fail coffeecake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Work the shortening into the dry mixture.
Dissolve the yeast in the cup of sweet milk, then add the beaten egg yolks to the milk mixture and add to the dry ingredient mixture.
Place in a bowl in the refrigerator overnight.
The next morning, beat the egg whites stiff and add the sugar cinnamon to this.
Divide the dough into 3 equal portions. Roll out 1/4-inch thick and spread 1/3 of the filling on each. Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place seam down on cookie sheet in the form of a crescent.
This makes 3 crescents.
Let stand exactly 1 hour and bake 40 minutes at 345°.

title: mango salsa
directions: Combine and chill.
Can use this with grilled meats and fish.

title: whole wheat yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a small bowl or cup; let stand 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix liquids and add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Mix in nuts, dates and raisins.
Grease and flour 4 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Divide between cans.
Place on lower oven rack and bake 1 hour at 325°. Let cool.
Remove from cans.
Freeze or serve.

title: popsicles
directions: Pour in ice cups and freeze.
Makes 20.

title: layered orange gelatin fluff
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water to orange concentrate to make 2 cups.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Chill until thick as unbeaten egg whites.
Spoon out 1 1/2 cups into a large bowl of mixer.
Set aside.

title: savory grilled potatoes
directions: Mix salad dressing and seasoning in large bowl until well blended.
Stir in potatoes and onion to coat.
Divide potato mixture evenly among six 12-inch square pieces of heavy-duty foil. Seal each to form packet.
Place foil packets on grill over medium-hot coals (coals will have slight glow).
Grill, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buttery corn bread
directions: Preheat oven according to Jiffy mix.
Mix according to Jiffy directions.
Place the butter or margarine in a baking pan and set in the preheated oven.
Let butter or margarine melt.
When melted, make sure the entire pan is covered with melted butter. Pour the excess butter or margarine into the corn bread mixture and stir until mixed in.
Pour mixture in the baking pan and cook according to Jiffy directions.

title: brown rice
directions: Cook celery, onion and bell pepper with margarine over low heat until tender.
Cook rice and beef consomme until tender.
Add remainder of cooked ingredients.

title: three way banana bread
directions: Place nuts in food processor and process at medium speed using momentary action to coarsely chop.
Set aside.
Place bananas in food processor and process until mashed at medium speed.
Remove and set aside.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Combine all ingredients, except meat, and mix well.
Add chicken to marinade and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Keep turning mixture for best results, at least 4 to 6 times.
Barbecue over mesquite coals for best results.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes on each side, being careful not to overcook.
Use remaining marinade to baste while cooking.
Remove to a cutting board and slice.

title: ham salad
directions: Grind bologna, cheese and eggs.
Add pickle relish.
Add mayonnaise and stir well.
Add sugar to desired taste.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Place in one-quart casserole.
Blend together soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir into broccoli.
Combine crumbs and butter or margarine; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix cookie crumbs with melted butter.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch cookie pan.
Spread soft ice cream on top of cookies. Freeze until firm.

title: new england brown bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine all-purpose flour, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl, combine whole wheat flour, buttermilk and molasses, adding this to the other flour mixture.
Mix well and stir in raisins.
Pour into well-greased 11.5 ounce coffee cans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until tested done.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Spread 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers.
Lay another layer of crackers over pudding.
Top with rest of pudding mixture.
Put another layer of crackers on top. Pour frosting over all.
Spreading to cover cake.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream together with 1/2 package of chipped beef (chopped). Top and cover with 1/2 package of chipped beef over the ball. Make day before using.

title: raven's "holiday spirits" pecan pound cake(or raven's "high spirits" pecan pound cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Have a 10-inch Bundt pan lightly greased and floured.

title: la la's cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: blueberry orange nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
In large bowl, beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Mix in eggs, milk, orange juice and peel.
Stir until blended.
Gradually stir in flour until blended.
Fold in blueberries and nuts.
Spoon batter in pan. Bake 1 hour or until done at 350° in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan, greased and floured.
Cool; wrap in foil overnight before icing.

title: brownie torte
directions: Butter and flour a 9-inch round cake pan.
In saucepan, heat butter and corn syrup until butter melts.
Stir in chips.
Stir until melted.
Add sugar and egg, blending well.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tested done. Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out on rack.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for about 50 minutes (325° in glass pan).

title: creole okra
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, until okra is tender.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream first 4
ingredients
well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture until all is incorporated.
Cover dough
with
plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts
or
slightly
smaller.
Place
on greased cookie sheet at least 1 inch apart.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes until very lightly browned; do
not
overbake.
Let cool slightly on pan, then remove to rack.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: epi's bread pudding
directions: Break croissants into bite-size pieces. Blend together half and half, sugar, vanilla and eggs. Place croissant pieces in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour liquid mixture over the croissants and let sit for 30 minutes. After rest of 30 minutes bake pudding in a 350° preheated oven for 35 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
In a 3-quart Dutch oven, saute meatballs until browned; drain and set aside.
Blend flour in hot drippings, stirring until smooth.
Cook over medium heat for 1 minute, stirring.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Combine everything and simmer, uncovered, 5 to 6 hours or until the meat has all become tender and shredded.
You may have to add a little water at the last.
It should not be runny.
Stir often.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Put through a food chopper zucchini, onions and peppers.
Add 5 tablespoons salt.
Put in a crock jar and let stand overnight.
The next day rinse and drain well.
Bring to a boil the next 7 ingredients.
When it starts to thicken, add vegetables and simmer for 32 minutes.
Put in sterile jars and seal.
Makes 5 or 6 pints. Very good!

title: apple cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla; pour over crust.
Toss apple with combined 1/3 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Spoon mixture over cream cheese layer; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Loosen cake from rim of pan.
Cool before removing rim.
Chill.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Chop unpeeled zucchini, shallots and garlic.
Put all three in heavy frying pan.
Cook for 10 to 20 minutes.
(Stir to keep from burning; you don't want to brown.)
Put all ingredients in blender and blend.
Add cream.
Serve hot with croutons or cold with chives.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer half the ham, potatoes and onions in a crock-pot. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put on half the cheese.
Repeat the layers again.
Spoon undiluted soup over the top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours or high for 4 hours.

title: corn chowder
directions: Thinly slice onion and saute in butter until cooked, not brown.
Add milk, corn, thyme, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1 hour.
Peel potatoes and dice.
Cook until done but firm; drain and add to soup.
Last, add cream.
Stir and serve.

title: hunter hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Season.
Peel and slice potatoes. Add 1/3 can water to the vegetable soup.
Layer hamburger, vegetable soup and potatoes in casserole dish.
Add 1/3 can water to mushroom soup.
Pour over ingredients.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until potatoes are tender.

title: easy gooey butter cake
directions: Beat together dry cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Spread into greased 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Beat together cream cheese, powdered sugar (reserve some for top of cake), vanilla and 2 eggs. Pour evenly over batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 35 minutes.
While cake is still warm, sprinkle with reserved sugar.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) paper or plastic cups.
For decorations: Gummy worms and frogs, candy flowers, chopped peanuts and granola.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Cool slightly.
Pour into two pie shells. Top with meringue made from the 4 egg whites and brown.

title: friend pat's swedish cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients except cabbage.
Boil cabbage until leaves are soft enough to separate from cabbage head.
Cut out hard stem from leaf.
Put stuffing in cabbage leaf and roll; secure with toothpicks.
Sprinkle each layer with cinnamon and lemon juice. Pour 1 large can of tomato juice plus juice from the can of tomatoes over cabbage rolls.
Cook slowly in oven for 2 hours. These can be frozen for later use.

title: bread sauce
directions: Put chopped onion into a frypan with butter.
Add pepper and salt.
Stir.
Add milk and bread crumbs; simmer over medium-low heat until sauce thickens a little.
Serve over chicken or fish.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix together flour, granulated sugar, soda, salt, egg, fruit and juice.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together brown sugar and walnuts.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: reception salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add juice from pineapple.
Blend cream cheese with small amount of pineapple juice.
When jello begins to congeal, add pineapple, cream cheese, celery, nuts, salt and whipped cream.
Mold.

title: deep-fried oreos
directions: Freeze cookies for 3 hours. Heat oil in a deep-fryer to 350°. Fix a sheet pan with paper towels for draining. Mix pancake mix and water and stir until smooth. When smooth, get cookies and dip each cookie, one at a time, into batter and make a smooth thin coat completely around the cookie. Place cookie in heated oil. Fry on both sides, turning over once until golden brown. Remove cookie from oil with metal tongs and drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Cool slightly before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1 cup nuts to roll balls in. Refrigerate.
Makes 2 small balls.

title: sweet potato hash browns
directions: Peel and shred white and sweet potatoes (enough to make 3 cups potatoes).
Add onions, 1 tablespoon
margarine, salt and pepper.
Place in a microwave-safe dish; add water and cover.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes.
Rotate dish every 2 minutes.
Stir and set aside.
When cool enough to handle, shape and press into 2 x 3 1/2-inch patties.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in a nonstick pan and fry hash browns over medium heat until golden brown on both sides.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
3 to 4 servings.
Approximately 145 calories per serving.

title: party pizza
directions: Brown the ground chuck and sausage; drain. Add the cheese. Stir until melted. Add the Worcestershire sauce, oregano, garlic salt and pepper.
Spread on party rye and freeze on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Grease a nine inch square baking dish or pan. Preheat oven to 350°. Into a large bowl, sift flour, sugar, 2 Tbsp. cocoa, baking powder and salt. Stir in milk, melted margarine and vanilla. Blend in walnuts. Spread in greased dish. Sprinkle brown sugar and 1/4 c. cocoa over batter in dish. Pour hot water over entire batter. Bake 35 - 40 minutes, or until batter is set and sauce bubbles. Let cool before slicing. (It makes its own chocolate sauce.) Enjoy with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream. Serves six.

title: kringla
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Work in Crisco with fingers until well blended.
In another bowl, beat egg, buttermilk, sour cream and sugar.
Stir into dry ingredients until well blended (it will be sticky!).
Scrape out on well floured board.
Sprinkle with flour and gently knead in more flour, if needed, so it can be easily handled.
The less flour, more tender Kringla.
Cut off a chunk and roll into a "pencil" 6-inches long.
Form into an 8 shape.
Bake on greased baking sheet (on bottom shelf) in 500° preheated oven, until bottom is light golden brown.
Change to top shelf and broil them until touched with color.
Watch carefully (take the phone off the hook!).
The hotter the oven, the quicker it becomes a tender Kringla.

title: shrimp fettuccine
directions: Saute onions, celery, pepper and garlic
in butter. Add shrimp, salt and cayenne pepper until shrimp is opaque.
Stir in flour, cheese and half and half, cook until cheese melts.
Stir in cooked fettucini and mix. Spoon into a 9 by 13 inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
This can be made and frozen.

title: hot dill pickles
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put cucumbers in jars.
Pour mixture 1/2-inch from top.
Seal jars.
Put in hot water bath for 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and bake or put in crock-pot until done.
Serve hot.

title: glazed strawberry-banana cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line pie shell with aluminum foil and fill with pie weights or dried beans.
Bake pie shell for 10 minutes.
Remove weights and bake for 10 minutes longer or until brown.
Set aside to cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and then add the sugar.
Mix well.
Add Karo syrup. Mix.
Add pecans and mix well.
Add butter, vanilla and salt. Mix.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: squash stir-fry
directions: Pour oil into iron frying pan or hot wok, coating sides until bottom is covered with oil.
Add garlic and onion; stir-fry 1 minute.
Stir in zucchini and yellow squash.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes (optional), salt and pepper. Stir well.
Sprinkle cheese over vegetables, stirring just until cheese melts.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: crab dip #1
directions: Melt cream cheese in double boiler.
Add all other ingredients.
Heat until bubbly.
Serve in chafing dish with assorted crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and blend sugars and shortening into a cream. Beat eggs slightly. Add eggs and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add to previous mixture and blend. Add oatmeal, corn flakes and coconut.
Mix by hand. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Bake less, if you wish them to be chewy.

title: ground beef and tater casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Combine beef, beans, soup, water, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine mashed potatoes and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon potato mixture in a mounded ring around top outer edge of casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top potatoes with cheese and remaining onion.
Bake another 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Mix together until soft.
Add walnuts and mix for crunch. Serve with apple slices or crackers.
Make it thinner and stuff celery or top cucumbers.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Combine and refrigerate until serving.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and milk; beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness*.

title: parmesan potato puffs
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain potatoes and mash. Add 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and next 4 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer just until mixture is smooth.
Stir in egg substitute.

title: ritz cookie
directions: Spread peanut butter between Ritz crackers and dip into melted white chocolate.
Cool.
This is a very good cookie.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onions in butter in saucepan until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes; stir often.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Cream cheese and butter.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, then milk.
Stir in lemon juice and peel.
Pour into graham cracker shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Cool before adding glaze.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Add flour, about 3 cups.
Roll out.
Dough will be sticky. Chill dough in refrigerator and it is easier to work with.

title: chili cabbage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook until cabbage is tender. Serves 4.

title: sugar coated pecans
directions: In bowl, beat egg whites and water until fluffy.
Add nuts to bowl.
Combine sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Pour over moist nuts. Generously butter baking sheet.
Place nuts on sheet and separate them.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: easy moussaka
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Slice unpeeled eggplant in 1/2-inch slices.
Melt shortening in skillet and brown eggplant. Remove eggplant and then saute beef until it crumbles and loses its color.

title: easy potato bake
directions: Butter a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients except corn flakes together.
Place in dish.
Crumble corn flakes over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well and chill before serving.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: orange-cinnamon ice cream pie
directions: In a medium bowl, thoroughly blend crumbs, margarine and sugar.
Press on bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Chill 1 hour.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper in skillet.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook until liquid is absorbed by rice.

title: pork chop potato bake
directions: Fill 9 x 13-inch baking dish 1/2 full of potatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle flour over potatoes.
Pour milk over potatoes.
Lay pork chops on top of potatoes; salt and pepper. Cook at 400° for 1 hour.
Turn pork chops once during baking time.

title: winnie's pickles
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard seed and celery seed.
Bring to boiling, stirring just until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Cool. Put in container.
Chill in refrigerator 24 hours to 1 month. Makes 7 cups.

title: play dough
directions: Add a small amount of water at a time until consistency of bread dough.
It will not be more than 1/2 cup.
Add food coloring, preferably to the water, before mixing.
Store in an airtight container or plastic bag.

title: good fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk together and let boil hard for 9 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into buttered pan and let cool completely.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and dip in small bowl; mix with electric mixer until smooth.
Spread mixture into bottom center
of dinner plate.
Make day before and refrigerate or put in freezer.
Brown beef and drain.
Combine beef with taco seasoning and water. Simmer about 10 minutes; cool to room temperature or in refrigerator.
Put mixture on top of cream cheese mixture and top with lettuce pieces.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with bag of Tortilla Chips.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples and arrange in 9-inch pie shell.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples. Sift 1/2 cup sugar with flour.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pour over apples. Bake in hot oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mashed potatoes, carrots and garlic
directions: Boil 5 cups potatoes, carrots and garlic.
Reduce to gentle boil, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes, or until tender.
Drain well.
Add milk, butter and salt.
Mash until vegetables are smooth.
Some small lumps of carrots may remain.

title: instant pudding icing
directions: Beat together pudding mix and milk; set aside.
In another bowl, put powdered sugar, Spry and vanilla; beat well.
Add and mix in the pudding mixture.
Ice your cake.

title: sponge cake (small)
directions: Separate eggs.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff. Beat egg yolks until stiff.
Add sugar, gradually beating.
Add lemon juice and beat once more.
Fold in egg whites and flour.
Do not beat.
Pour in ungreased pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: cowboy or dude spuds
directions: Thaw potatoes before mixing, they mix better.
Mix the first 8 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole.
Put 1/4 cup melted oleo and crushed potato chips over the top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
I've served this to the branding crew and also to guests and everyone loved it!

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour cold on onions and cucumbers. Put in refrigerator and stir once each day for three days.
Keep in refrigerator, in glass container.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour, Crisco and salt with pastry blender.
Beat egg slightly and put in 1 cup measuring cup.
Add vinegar and fill rest of measuring cup up with water.
Mix with flour mixture and roll out on floured board.
Makes 3 (2 crust) pies or 6 single crusts. For single crusts, bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Bake 2 crust filled pies for 30 minutes at 425°.

title: frozen fruit mold
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve liquid and measure. Add water to make 2 1/4 cups.
Combine pudding mix, sugar and 1/4 cup pineapple syrup in saucepan.
Add egg and blend well. Stir in remaining syrup.
Stir over medium heat until comes to full boil. Remove from heat and cover with wax paper.
Chill.

title: colored popcorn
directions: Use an electric popper or a large covered saucepan on the stove.

title: fruit salad(club member:  lee higginbotham)
directions: Stir together and refrigerate.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peach slices in bottom of 1-quart casserole.
Mix brown sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and salt.
Pour over peaches.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients, cut in shortening.
Add milk to make soft dough and mix slightly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on top of peaches.
Bake in preheated oven until browned.

title: beef stew with cheddar dumplings
directions: Select a prime rib roast, well marbleized.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Season roast with salt and pepper.
Place in a shallow roasting pan.
Do not cover or add water.
Put in oven and cook for 1 hour.

Turn off oven, but do not open oven or peek at any time until ready to serve. Regardless of length of time roast has been in the oven, turn oven to 375° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes before serving it.
Roast will be brown, crisp and beautifully pink all the way through, medium rare and juicy.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: Melt butter in a heavy 4-quart pan.
Add flour.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add broth. Add next 7 ingredients.
Return to heat and bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
In small bowl, blend egg yolk and cream.
Gradually blend in several spoonfuls of hot soup.
Return all to saucepan.
Stir and simmer 15 minutes. Add cheese until melted.

title: mali veggie rice
directions: Cook the rice.
Wash the tomato, mushrooms and green pepper. Cut the mushrooms in half and mince the green pepper. Peel and slice the onion.
Melt the butter in the skillet and saute the onion until soft.
Add the other vegetables, tomato paste, salt, cayenne and curry powder.
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring.
Stir in the cooked rice and serve.

title: cheddar bay biscuits
directions: Combine Bisquick|, milk and Cheddar; beat with a wooden spoon for about 30 seconds.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Smooth tops down with spoon.
Bake in 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Combine butter and garlic powder; pour over hot biscuits.
Serves 8.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle pecans on top of coconut.
Pour cake batter on top of pecans.
Melt butter, cream cheese and sugar in saucepan over low heat until melted.
Pour over cake batter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, salt and 1/4 cup milk.
Add eggs and 1/4 cup milk and stir.
Add Schnapps and stir.
Add apples and stir.
Cover bottom of baking dish with butter and pour mixture on top.
Bake at 425° about 1/2 hour.
Dust with powdered sugar. Serve hot, warm or cold.

title: coconut cake
directions: Kream sugah 'n buttah...add beat up aig yolks...mix gud...sift flour'n bakin' powder...now add flour mixture 'n milk alternately to sugar mixture...mix 'n pore in 3 pans...bake at 350° until done...'bout 30 minutes.

title: homemade glazed icing
directions: Mix sugar, cream and syrup until combined well. Pour in heavy pan and cook over medium heat until mixture reaches soft-ball stage. Try not to stir while mixture is heating. Once soft-ball stage is reached, remove from heat and beat until spreading consistency is reached. Placing pan in cold water will speed this process.

title: mixed vegetable pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with a nonfat cooking spray. Place over medium heat until hot.
Add the broccoli and the next 3 ingredients; saute 4 minutes.
Add pepper strips and mushrooms; saute 4 minutes longer.
Add pasta, tomato and vermouth; toss gently.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with cheese, parsley and pepper flakes; toss gently.
Serve immediately. Yields 9 servings.
Contains 2.3 g fat.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil together.
Add cake and pudding mixes and the hot water (be sure to add the hot water a little at a time while beaters are running).
Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed. Stir in poppy seed.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° in a tube or Bundt pan.
Sift with powdered sugar on top while still warm.

title: easy oven broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well.
Stir in sour cream and soup mix; mix until well blended.
Spoon into baking dish.
In a small bowl, mix cracker crumbs and butter or margarine.
Sprinkle over broccoli mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix all other ingredients in separate bowl.
Add to dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Mix water and sugar.
Place over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add fruit juices and bananas mixing well.
Cool and freeze until firm.
Serve.
Thaw until mushy.
Add ginger ale. Makes approximately 35 servings.
More ginger ale can be used.

title: chocolate bark
directions: Line a baking sheet with foil.
Place saltines on foil covering entire surface.
Melt margarine in saucepan; add brown sugar. Pour margarine/sugar mixture over crackers.
Bake in oven until bubbly for about 5 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven. Immediately place chocolate chips on hot mixture.
Spread evenly. Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: grannie's biscuits
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in sifter; sift.
Put 1/2 of the shortening in baking pan and other 1/2 in the sifted flour mixture.
Cut in the shortening.
Add the buttermilk.
Stir and dump onto a floured surface, quickly.
Knead to a smooth ball, quickly.

title: sole in almond shrimp sauce
directions: Poach fillets in wine in a 350° oven until fish flakes easily with a fork, but is still moist, 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Reserve 1/4 cup shrimp; mash remaining with 2 tablespoons butter and set aside.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 X 9 inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine: mix together and press into pan.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients: press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: bread bowl with dill dip
directions: Hollow out bread in shape of a bowl. Set aside.
Save bread chunks as "dunkers."
Shred beef into small pieces and mix well with remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Pour into bread bowl. Arrange dunkers around bowl.
I usually cut up extra bread for dunkers. Eat bowl when dunkers are gone.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add frozen orange juice, stirring until completely dissolved.
Chill until slightly runny.
Add pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and pecans. Pour in 11 x 8 pan.
Chill until set.
Serve on lettuce leaf and top with mayonnaise (optional).

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
When well mixed, add nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Don't overbake.

title: venison strips
directions: Trim all fat from venison.
Partially freeze steak for easy slicing.
Cut into paper-thin slices.
Seed green pepper, slice into thin rounds.
Heat margarine in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook for 5 minutes or until onion is transparent.
Stir frequently.
Remove to heated plate with slotted spoon.
Heat additional butter in skillet if necessary.
Add venison strips in single layer.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Cook over medium high heat for 1 minute, turn strips over.
Cook for 2 minutes longer.
Add peppers and onion.
Cook for several minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Do not overcook. Serve immediately.

title: red pepper bisque
directions: Saute peppers, leeks and onions in butter until onion is transparent.
Add broth and cream.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Puree in blender.
Return to saucepan and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add salt to taste.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rice consomme
directions: Saute onion in oleo in baking dish.
Pour uncooked rice over butter and onion in dish. Pour consomme over all. Bake at 375° to 400° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Place cabbage and onion in saucepan.
Add enough water to cover cabbage.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and cook until fork-tender.
In another saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Add and stir in flour.
Blend well.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir mixture over medium heat until it thickens.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Drain cabbage mixture.
Add and stir the cabbage mixture into seasoned sauce. Heat to boiling and serve.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli as directed. Add garlic powder. In large pot, melt butter and saute onions until tender. Add 2 cans of chicken broth and boil. Cook noodles in broth. Add broccoli with juices, then cheese and half and half. Lower heat and cook until melted. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate cake(aunt nettie's)
directions: Mix together and put in two round tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or less.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: chili italian-style(makes about 2 quarts)
directions: In large kettle, brown meat with onion; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered 30 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: the big dipper
directions: Dice Ro-Tel tomatoes & green chilies.
Reserve 1 Tbsp (drained) for garnish.
Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat just until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Serve warm with assorted raw vegetable dippers and toasted French bread slices. Garnish dip with reserved tomatoes, red pepper and (optional) green onion if desired.
Makes 4 cups.

title: corn-bean casserole
directions: Mix together; pour in dish.

title: rancho beans
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add all other ingredients; mix well. Pour into casserole dish (about 2-quart size).
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or 350° for 1 hour.

title: wanda's dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with corn tortilla chips.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Keep in refrigerator. Stir before serving.

title: dawn's nachos
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and drain.
Prepare the taco and chili mixes according to the packages.

title: pina colada shake(low calorie)
directions: In a blender, blend milk and extract.
Add frozen banana and pineapple chunks, a few at a time.
Add ice cubes one at a time. Blend until smooth.
Serves 1.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Mix together with fork or in a food chopper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice in 2 1/2 cups chicken broth for 20 minutes.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into large casserole dish.
Cover top with 1 stack of Ritz crackers mixed with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: bread pudding(serves 6)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 30 minutes at 350° in buttered Pyrex dish.
Will rise like souffle.

title: corn flakes drops
directions: Cook sugar and Karo syrup on low heat.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in corn flakes until all coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Let cool and they will harden.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and syrup together.
Add sugar, butter, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well and pour into pastry shell that has been heated in oven and pressed down.
If you heat the pie crust, it will cook better.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine rice, ham, onion, green pepper, pimento, celery, Miracle Whip and black pepper.
Layer this mixture and broccoli.
Combine soup and cheese.
Pour over top and cover with potato chips.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: tassies
directions: Mix as pie crust and make 24 to 36 balls.
Press into ungreased tea size pans.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Press into dough slightly.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cake cool completely before icing.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Make 2 cake layers and split to make four layers.
Put filling between and on top of layers.
Soaks in good.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Bake chicken, then cut into pieces.
Put in shallow 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream and garlic salt.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Mix cracker crumbs, poppy seeds and margarine.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Combine celery soup, milk and turkey.
Pour into pan.
Make stuffing using margarine and turkey broth.
Cover turkey mixture with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 as a main dish.
A perfect use for leftover holiday turkey.

title: pineapple pepper chicken
directions: In a saucepan, combine the first 10 ingredients; stir until smooth. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Brown chicken in a skillet, or quickly grill. Place in a 9 x 9 inch greased baking dish sprayed with Pam. Pour reserved sauce over chicken. Bake, uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes. Add pineapple chunks and green pepper strips. Bake 15 minutes longer or until heated through. Serve with rice. Yields 4 servings. This recipe easily doubles or triples for 8 or 12 servings.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in soup and milk. Heat thoroughly.
Garnish with shredded cheese, diced, cooked ham or bacon, if desired.
Yield:
2 1/2 quarts.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all except 7-Up.
Beat well. Add 7-Up; mix well. Bake in cookie sheet pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mom's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done, tear off bones.
Mix butter, melted, with dressing.
Use a little of half to line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken over dressing.
Mix broth and soups together. Pour over chicken.
Put the rest of dressing in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sunday orange cake
directions: Melt butter; add grated orange peel and eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Add dry cake mix, stir.
Add oil, orange juice (thawed) and water.
Mix well.
Add Jell-O.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: simple sauteed asparagus
directions: Break ends of asparagus off by holding the tip in one hand and the stalk end in the other and bending stalk until it breaks. Stalk will break off where the tender part begins.
Place the tips in a pot of well-salted boiling water.
Blanch for 3 minutes. Drain and pat dry.
Cut on the diagonal into 1 inch pieces.
Heat the oil in a large skillet over high heat.
Saute the asparagus, tossing for 1 1/2 minutes, until just crisp-tender.
Off the heat, toss in vinegar and salt to taste.

title: triple ambrosia salad
directions: Pour boiling liquid over gelatin in bowl, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Add orange sherbet, stir until melted. Stir in 1 can of the oranges.
Pour into 6-cup ring mold; chill until firm.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put sugar, sifted flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon in bowl and stir well.
Beat eggs and add cooking oil.
Add this to the first ingredients.
Add diced apples, vanilla and pecans. Stir well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken mushroom gravy
directions: Remove skin and extra fat from chicken.
Boil chicken in mixture about 50 minutes or until done.
Stir in cornstarch and water to thicken; serve.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix shortening and brown sugar and eggs.
Add sour milk.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Stir in shortening mixture, add pecans, cherries and dates.
Chill dough overnight.
Will keep a long time in refrigerator.
You can bake part of them at a time.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased baking tray.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: apple topped pie
directions: Gradually beat milk into cheese in a large bowl until smooth. Add pudding mixes and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Beat one or two minutes.
Pour in pie crust.
Mix apples and other 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon in a small bowl.
Sweeten to taste.
Spoon over pudding mixture.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or until set.
Store in refrigerator.

title: crunchy topped casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook bacon until crisp; remove bacon from skillet and crumble. Drain fat, reserving 2 tablespoons. Saute onion and celery until tender.
Add beefaroni, crumbled bacon, vegetables and 1 cup cheese; mix well.
Spoon mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Combine corn chips and 1 cup shredded cheese. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Serves six.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in greased muffin tins in 425° oven for ten minutes.
For smaller batch, use half ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cover 13 x 9-inch baking dish with 1 can cream of chicken soup.
Cover with broccoli.
Add another layer of cream of chicken soup.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Add layer of cream of mushroom soup.
Sprinkle parsley on top of soup.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: gratineed ziti
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion and garlic in oil until onion is soft.
Break up tomatoes and add with juice to skillet.
Stir in crushed red pepper.
Increase heat and boil sauce.
Stir until liquid has evaporated (about 18 minutes).
Season with salt and pepper.
Keep warm.

title: brunswick stew(this recipe makes a lot so you may want to cut it in half.)
directions: Cook Boston butt until falling apart.
You want it good and tender.
Add everything else and cook on low heat until done.
It will be done when the potatoes are tender.

title: salmon and corn chowder
directions: Melt the butter in a large saucepan over low heat; add the leeks and cook, stirring frequently, until very soft but not browned (about 8 minutes).
