Add the potato to the leeks and stir to coat with butter.
Pour in the stock and simmer, uncovered, over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add the milk and cream; simmer for 10 minutes more.
Add the salmon and corn; simmer just until the fish and corn are done, about 5 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve hot!
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water until tender. Drain, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Make sauce in skillet by combining butter, flour, milk and reserved liquid.
Cook until sauce is as thick as heavy cream.
Add salt, 1/2 cup grated cheese, pepper and squash mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish. Top with remaining cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: recipe for raising a child
directions: Add:
firm arms, gentle direction, loving looks, soft words, understanding, interest, patience, squeeze frequently.
Mix with family fun and lots of laughter.
Surround with security and warmth.
Keep at even temperature until well set and molded.
Turn out with confidence to explore the exciting world around them.

title: almond float fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup water.
Heat evaporated milk, remaining water and 1/2 cup sugar to just below boiling.
Add gelatin to hot mixture and stir until completely mixed.
Cool. Add almond extract.
Pour into a flat pan and refrigerate.
When solid, cut into cubes.
Combine the chilled fruit mixture with syrup and the almond cubes.

title: uncle tom's fireside coffee
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use 2 tablespoons per cup of boiling water.

title: pie crust
directions: Put in bowl flour, salt and sugar; cut in shortening.
Add egg.
Mix vinegar and water together and add to flour mixture.

title: chocolate sandwich cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cake mix, oil and eggs and mix well. Roll into small balls and place 2 inches apart on ungreased pan. Do not flatten. Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes and remove from pan.

title: 24-hour fruit salad
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt, lemon juice, pineapple juice and butter and
cook in a double boiler until thick.
Cool and pour over
drained
fruit.
Whip the cream, then fold in fruit mixture. Chill 24 hours.

title: lazy man's pie
directions: Melt oleo in pan or baking dish that you are going to make pie in.

title: john mozetti
directions: Put a tablespoon or so of oil (can be olive oil) or drippings in heavy skillet.
Heat and then add ground beef; cook until lightly browned.
Add onion, green pepper and seasonings and continue cooking until vegetables are tender.
Add soup and tomatoes; simmer for 15 or 20 minutes.
Add water chestnuts. Check seasonings.
You may prefer to add a little more garlic powder, pepper, etc.

title: eskimo cookies(a no-bake delight)
directions: Soften butter; beat well.
Add sugar and mix.
Stir in water, vanilla and cocoa powder.
Add oats gradually and mix.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Shape into balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: salsa
directions: Mix together all ingredients.

title: piroghi's
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll dough out thin. Cut medium circles out; spoon filling into center of dough and pinch edges together. (Filling can be anything you want.) Place in boiling water for approximately 2 to 3 minutes. When ready to serve, fry in skillet with butter and fresh chopped onions.

title: fruit custard
directions: Drain fruit, reserving syrups.
Cut pears in half lengthwise. Measure syrups to make 1 1/2 cups.
Combine fruit syrups, lemon juice, salt and cornstarch in small saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Add Sweet 'n Low.
Add small amount of hot mixture to well beaten egg and blend thoroughly.
Return to hot mixture and add grated lemon peel. Cool.
Place small amount of lemon custard in bottom of 4 sherbet glasses.
Arrange 4 pear slices, spoke fashion, in custard. Divide remaining custard over pears.
Garnish with 2 orange segments.
Chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: applesauce raisin cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl combine spice cake mix, raisins, cooking oil, applesauce and egg; beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake cookies at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Crust:
Cut sugar cookie dough (do not roll) into 1/2-inch slices and place on a pizza pan, approximately 1-inch apart.
Bake according to package directions.
Let cool completely.

title: 7 layer dinner
directions: In Dutch oven, combine all vegetables and onion.
Press hamburger on top.
Pour soup over and bake until vegetables are done.

title: ginger snaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add egg, molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and add all together. Form into 1 in. balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° 12-12 min.
They burn easily, don't over cook. If dough is too sticky, put in regrigerator.

title: cranberry pear pie
directions: In saucepan, combine cranberries and water.
Bring to boil and simmer 3 minutes.
Mix sugar, cornstarch an cinnamon and add to hot cranberries.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Gently stir in pears.

title: mary anne's brownies
directions: Add 1/2 cup sugar into eggs and beat until smooth. Combine remaining sugar, oil and melted chocolate.
Stir into egg mixture. Add vanilla. Sift flour and measure.
Add salt and blend into creamed mixture. Add nuts and beat thoroughly until smooth.
Line two greased 8-inch shallow pans.
Pour mixture into pans and bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine and chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except powdered sugar; blend well.
Chill dough 30 minutes. Heat oven to 325°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in powdered sugar (coat heavily).
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes, or until edges are set.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: no-knead parmesan garlic bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, margarine, sugar, eggs and salt.
Stir in 1 cup of the flour.
Stir in remaining flour and continue stirring, scraping down from side of bowl, until soft, sticky dough forms.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.
(Dough is ready if indentation remains when touched.)
Stir down dough by beating 25 strokes.

title: granola bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil; grease.
In large bowl combine all ingredients except condensed milk and margarine.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pat mixture evenly into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly; remove from pan and peel off foil.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: please the crowd potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, then peel and dice them.
Drizzle butter over diced potatoes.
Add salt, pepper, and green onions to potatoes. Stir.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13 inch pan and top with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: italian round steak
directions: Rub flour, salt and pepper into round steak.
Brown in a skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender.
Serve over noodles or rice, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix butter and crumbs and place in 9-inch square pan.
Place the coconut, chocolate morsels and nuts in pan in order given. Pour milk over mixture and smooth out evenly.

title: autumn garden cheese soup
directions: Saute 1 medium onion until lightly browned in 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup pine nuts to skillet of onions and stir rapidly, taking special care not to burn them.
Lift the skillet off the burner and shake as they begin to brown.
Use either a vegetable stock made from water leftover from boiling vegetables in a previous meal or a meat stock from a previous meal or foul dish.
(If you are in a hurry, just use 2 to 4 cups of water and let the onions and pine nuts form most of the flavor.)

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Rinse and scrub potatoes.
Pat dry.
Prick a few times with a fork.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until soft.
Cut a thin slice off the top of each potato.
Carefully scoop out the pulp. Put in a bowl.
Separate eggs.
Add egg yolks to potato pulp. Stir and blend until smooth.
Add butter and cream.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Fold into potato mixture.
Fill potato shells with mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in oven at 375° for about 15 minutes or until heated through.
For variation; add chopped sauteed onion, chopped chives or parsley, thinly sliced pepper or sauteed mushrooms to potato mixture.
Season to taste with mustard, curry powder or nutmeg.

title: crunchy chicken breasts
directions: Put a slice of cheese on each breast.
Spoon soup over cheese and a slice of tomato over soup.
Sprinkle crouton mixture on top. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a large salad bowl about 7 to 8 inches high on sides, arrange leaves of washed and patted dry romaine lettuce around sides of salad bowl.
Place macaroni shells, grated fresh sharp cheese and cooked ham cubes in next.
Add frozen small peas.
Top with cherry tomatoes and wedged egg slices.
Cool in refrigerator until ready.

title: eazy clam chowder
directions: Saute onions and celery in oil until tender. Add potatoes and 4 cups water. Simmer 15 minutes. Add clams. Mix powdered milk with 1 cup water in separate bowl. Add milk, butter and salt to clam mixture. Pour into ovenproof dish. Garnish with bacon. Serve hot.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Combine the graham crackers with the sugar and melted butter.

title: german cherry cake
directions: Mix together and take out 1 cup for topping.

title: classic spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
In medium bowl, stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts, green onions, lemon juice and Parmesan cheese.
Cover; refrigerate 2 hours.
If desired, serve with pumpernickel bread, crackers or vegetables.
Makes 3 cups.

title: tater-topped casserole(is a wonderful potluck dinner item)
directions: Brown ground beef and pour off excess fat.
Put meat in casserole.
Spread vegetables over meat.
Spread soup on top vegetables.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Top with potatoes. Season each layer as desired (I use garlic powder).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: yule tiding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Bake in bread pan with paper. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: user friendly freezer tomato sauce
directions: Combine onion, celery, green pepper, garlic and water in 2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with casserole lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on full power for 6 to 7 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring once.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, salt, chili powder, basil and oregano.
Cover. Microwave on full power for 30 to 35 minutes or until thickened, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Cool.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute all but last 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, 50 to 60 minutes.
Add olives.
Serve immediately.

title: brandied yams
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water to cover 45 minutes or until tender; cool to touch. Peel and mash potatoes.
Stir in next 7 ingredients; spoon into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Brush top with butter; sprinkle with orange rind. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; add garnish.
Serves 8.

title: potato and onion casserole
directions: Shred potatoes, onions and cheese and mix together in casserole dish.
Beat eggs and add milk, salt and pepper.
Add egg mixture to potato mixture.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality. Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc., and check the rum again. It must be just right to be sure the rum if of the highest quality.
Pour 1 level cup of rum into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat the procedure.
With an electric mixer, beat 1 cup butter in a large fluffy bowl; add 1 seaspoon of tugar and beat again.
Meanwhile, to make sure rum hasn't gone bad, drink 1 cup.
Open second quart, if necessary.
Add large eggs and 2 cups fried druit and beat until high.
If the druit gets stuck in beaters, just pry it loose with screwscriber.
Sample rum again.
Check for quality and tonsisticity.
Sift 3 cups baking powder, pinch of rum, seaspoon of toda and a cup of talt or pepper (whatever).
Sample rum again.
Shift 1/2 pint of lemon juice; fold in chopped butter and strained nuts.
Add tablespoon of brown tugar, or whatever color you can find.
Mix well.
Grease oven and turn cake pan to 350°.
Now pour whole mess into oven, or better yet, forget the oven.
Check rum again and go to bed.

title: pasta bean soup(microwave)
directions: In large bowl, stir all ingredients.
Divide soup mixture among four 1-pint microwave heatable bowls.
Cover with lid; freeze.
To heat one serving frozen soup, microwave in covered heatable bowl on High 4 1/2 minutes or until hot, stirring once during heating.

title: microwave potato wedges
directions: Cut each potato into 8 wedges.
Combine water and next 4 ingredients in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Add potato wedges, tossing to coat.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at high 8 minutes of until tender, stirring after 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and salt.
Yield:
4 servings.
Low fat recipe.

title: chocolate cobbler
directions: Combine the flour, sugar and cocoa.
Stir in milk and oil until smooth.
Pour in lightly greased 8 inch square pan. Then mix 1 cup packed brown sugar and 1/4 cup baking cocoa together and sprinkle over the batter.
Then pour 1 3/4 cups hot water over top of cake mixture.
DO NOT STIR!
Bake at 350 for 40-45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
There will be a juicy syrup on the bottom.
Serve warm plain or with ice cream.

title: busy day stew
directions: Mix preserves and Russian dressing until smooth and creamy. Add soup mix and stir over a very low flame until well blended. Do not boil.
Pour over chicken and bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Uncover and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Baste often.

title: sumi salad
directions: Mix cabbage and onion, refrigerate.
Add remaining ingredients 20 minutes before serving.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter and sugar; add vanilla.
Mix in flour and crushed potato chips.
Blend with other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets; flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: just the best cookies
directions: Cream sugars, margarine, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda and salt well.
Stir into creamed mixture, blending well. Stir in oatmeal, cornflake crumbs, coconut and pecans.
Mix well. Cover mixing bowl and chill dough at least 1 hour.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with a small glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: fun fruit cocktail
directions: Combine cottage cheese, fruit cocktail (drained) and powdered jello. Mix well.
Lightly fold in Cool Whip with a spoon until all is mixed.
Chill for 2
hours before serving.
Enjoy!

title: vicki's fish brine
directions: Mix above ingredients in large pot. Boil for 20 minutes, stirring often. Chill in refrigerator.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix beef, onions and soup together and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover mixture with a layer of cheese slices, then cover with your favorite pie crust.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: gulf shores red snapper(southern fried)
directions: Send husband to Gulf Shores on annual church fishing trip. Cut fillets in half lengthwise.
Soak in cold water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Drain fish.
Batter fish very well in meal mixture. Deep fry in Crisco oil until golden brown.
These are good fried in an iron skillet.

title: gob cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; divide into two jelly roll pans.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: hidden valley ranch vegetables
directions: Combine dry salad dressing mix with oil in large casserole. Add vegetables and toss to coat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Add butter, onion and garlic to pot.
Let simmer a few minutes then add water and cubes.
Bring to a boil.
Add pasta. Let cook 5 minutes, then add broccoli.
Let cook 5 minutes, then serve.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Mix first 4 ingredients; cut in oleo.
Add eggs and milk mixture.
Fold in blueberries; bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until a little brown in muffin tins lined with baking cups.

title: cranberry pear bread pudding
directions: Place the cranberries in a small bowl and pour the eau de vie over them.
Peel, core and slice pears into six pieces each.
Melt the butter in a large skillet over medium heat and, when it ceases foaming, add 1/4 cup sugar and the pears along with the eau de vie and cranberries.
Cook, stirring gently until the sugar melts and the mixture is warm.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Whisk eggs, then whisk in the remaining sugar, half and half and vanilla.
Lightly butter a baking dish and line it with bread, overlapping the slices slightly.
Distribute the pear mixture over the bread, the pour the custard over.
Let the pudding rest for about 15 minutes, then set the dish in a water bath.
Bake the pudding for about 45 minutes, until it is set but not dry.
Serve warm or at room temperature, dusted with confectioners' sugar.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Brown meatballs and drain.
Mix chili sauce and cranberry sauce together. Add meatballs and stir.
Cook in crock-pot until heated thoroughly on high, approximately 2 to 3 hours.

title: monkey pie
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add onions.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Pour off excess oil.
Spray casserole dish or oil lightly by hand.
Spoon beef and onions into dish, then stir in the corn or peas, undrained.
Pat mixture flat and spread the already mashed potatoes on top.
Arrange cheese slices on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts completely and browns.
Remove and serve.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water and let cool.
Mix with other ingredients and serve.
Freeze orange and lemon slices and use instead of ice.
Serves 20 people.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In Pyrex dish, melt margarine.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, flour and milk, then pour on top of margarine.
Put fruit on top of mixture.
Sprinkle cinnamon or brown sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve eggs.
Remove yolks.
Press yolks with fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix with fork until smooth.
Lightly mound into egg whites.

title: cocoons
directions: Mix well.
Roll out in rolls about the size of a finger. Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°.
Roll in confectioners sugar as soon as you take them out of the oven.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk and egg yellows.
Add water.
Add flavoring.
Cook until thick while stirring constantly over low heat.
Remove from stove.
Put mixture into 2 baked pie shells.
Cool.
Top with egg whites.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter (at room temperature, but not soft).
Add sugar gradually.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add egg one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in water; add to buttermilk.
Add salt and flavorings.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately; blend well.
Spray tube pan with Baker's Joy.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 325° to 350° for approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into small thin strips. Brown round steak, garlic and onions in small amount of oil; add mushrooms. Stir in tomato soup until well blended. Stir in sour cream and simmer for one hour.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water and drain. Prepare sauce following directions. Add meat mixture; cover and cook about 10 minutes. In greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2 baking dish, layer half of each the noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella, and sauce. Repeat. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before eating. Makes 4 servings.

title: jello salad with fruit
directions: Mix lime and orange Jell-O with water.
Add lime sherbet and jell slightly.
Add sliced bananas, drained pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Fold in whipped cream.
Mold in cake pan.

title: angel pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and cornstarch and stir until thick.
Add remaining ingredients to hot mixture while hot, beating all the time.
When cool, place in baked pie crust and put 1/2 pint whipped cream on top.
Sprinkle crushed peppermint candy on top. Place in refrigerator.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 400° for 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Saute onion in butter; add spinach, stirring well.
Cook 2 minutes.
Blend flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Add to spinach.
Combine eggs, half and half and cheese.
Add to spinach mixture.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.

title: yummy rice pizza
directions: Combine rice and water; cook until done or water is absorbed. Fold in eggs and 3/4 pound grated cheese.
Pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until firm and set. Remove from oven and top with ground beef.
Cover with spaghetti sauce and sprinkle 2 pounds grated cheese on top.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Return to oven.
Bake at 350° for an additional 20 minutes.

title: delicious cake
directions: Cook mincemeat with 1/2 cup water.
Stir well, cooking until mix is almost dry (3 minutes).
Cool and set aside.
Mix shortening and dry ingredients into bowl.
Add eggs, syrup and 1/4 cup water; beat 2 minutes.
Add cooled mincemeat, beating 1 minute more.
Bake in 8-inch square pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top with powdered sugar and water glaze with slivered almonds.
Very moist cake, spicy a He Man cake.

title: loaf bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water (1 1/4 cups); leave it for 5 minutes.
Put 2 cups water in bowl.
Add sugar, salt, shortening and 2 cups flour to make paste.
Add softened yeast and flour until stiff.
Rest mixture 10 minutes.
Sift in more flour; knead 10 minutes.
Put in greased pan; let rise 2 hours.
Knead.
Let rise 1 hour more.
Shape in loaves; rest.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Butter top; let cool on table.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients into a small bowl; stir and set aside.
Combine sugar and oil; beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Add egg and beat well.
On low speed, add flour and banana; blend well.
Pour into a 8 x 4 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creole eggplant
directions: Wash eggplants; cut in halves lengthwise.
Remove pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Chop pulp.
Combine bacon, onion, green pepper and mushrooms in large skillet.
Saute until bacon is crisp.
Add eggplant pulp, tomato, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 10 minutes.
Place eggplant shells in 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan.
Place hot mixture into shells.
Add 1/2 inch water. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine rice, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper; chill overnight. Combine chicken, celery, green pepper, peas and mayonnaise.
Stir in rice mixture.
Chill several hours.
Serves 8.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and margarine.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Add eggs, sugars, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Bake in a large pan, greased and floured, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Fry chicken and set aside to drain.
Put the vinegar, sugar, leftover pineapple juice and water in pan; stir constantly until it boils.
Add pineapple chunks and carrots.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop the corn in popper.
Keep warm.
Measure remaining ingredients into saucepan.
Stir until sugar is dissolved over medium heat.
Cook, without stirring, to 270°, or until a small amount of mixture becomes brittle when dropped into very cold water.
Pour syrup over popcorn, stirring corn to mix well. Butter hands and press corn into balls.
Wrap to keep crisp.

title: oven bag rabbit
directions: Shake flour, salt and pepper in 10 x 16-inch oven cooking bag and place in 2-inch deep roasting pan.
Add rabbit pieces and shake to coat meat. Spread out rabbit pieces in bottom of the bag. Add onion, celery and butter; combine with wine and Kitchen Bouquet before adding to bag.
Secure bag with tie and make 6 half-inch slits in the top of the bag.
Bake one hour or until tender.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: rocky road pie
directions: Mix pudding with 1 2/3 cups milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle M&M's on top.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo.
Add eggs one at a time and mix well.
Add vinegar, vanilla and coconut.
Blend well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pear honey
directions: Chop pears fine or put through grinder.
There should be 5 cups.
Put in large pot.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook over low heat 35 to 40 minutes, stirring constantly. Fruit should be clear and liquid thick.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal by processing in a boiling water bath for 10 minutes. Makes 6 pints.

title: medley of vegetables
directions: Mix vegetables together in covered baking dish.
Melt butter. Add salt, sugar, pepper and tapioca.
Mix. Add tomatoes and mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until vegetables are fork-tender.

title: baked beans
directions: If time permits, place ingredients in casserole
or bean pot, topped with bacon strips and cook 4 hours at 300°.
If time is short, saute all fresh vegetables in seasoned fat.
Add all remaining ingredients and cook at 300° for 2 hours.
Do not cook too dry as juices will thicken some when removed from oven. Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: orange whip
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add orange juice.
Chill until almost set.
Beat until fluffy.
Fold in yogurt.
Add sweetener to taste.
Pour into individual serving dishes.
Garnish with fresh orange slices.
Makes 3 cups.

title: 7-cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix and bake in greased bread tins at 350° for about 55 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Stir chicken, vegetables, and soup in ungreased 2 qt. casserole dish.
Stir remaining ingredients until blended.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake uncovered about 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: cold vegetable pizza
directions: Press 8 crescent rolls into a round pizza pan and bake for the crust.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Ranch dressing and mayo over cooled crust.
Cut up your vegetables to size desired.
Use any vegetables you like.
I use ham and pepperoni to spice it up. Chill if desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix Parkay and Velveeta cheese; melt together.
Add all other ingredients and bake in a shallow pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo syrup and water in heavy skillet.
Cook about 10 minutes (until you see a white string thread), stirring occasionally.
Add peanuts; cook about 8 minutes or until mixture turns light caramel color (stir constantly).
Add margarine and stir real fast until margarine melts.
Add baking soda; stir until well mixed.
Pour onto a heavily buttered platter or cookie sheet. Let cool then break into pieces.

title: crawfish carola with angel hair pasta
directions: Saute onions and garlic in margarine until clear.
Add crawfish tails and flour.
Mix well, then add mushrooms, cream soup, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add sour cream just before serving over angel hair pasta.

title: paradish punch
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Chill.
Serve in punch bowl with an attractive ice mold.
Yield: 2 gallons.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Steep tea in water and remove bags.
Add sugar and spices and simmer 10 minutes.
Add all juices and simmer another 10 minutes. Serve hot.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: corn meal muffins
directions: Sift flour into mixing bowl.
Add the next 4 ingredients and re-sift.
Combine shortening, milk and egg.
Mix well.
Pour all at once into center of dry ingredients.
Stir quickly until dry ingredients are just dampened.
Then stir 3 or 4 times more. Batter will not be smooth.
Spoon quickly into greased muffin pans.
Fill about 2/3 full.
Bake about 25 minutes in a 425° oven or until golden brown.
Serve hot with butter.
Very good!

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a greased casserole dish.
Sit in a pan of water and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together. Mix in all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or simmer in skillet on stove.

title: vermicelli pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain vermicelli.
Combine Italian dressing and salad seasoning.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serves 12.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Grease baking dish, 11 x 8 x 2-inches. Crumble crackers in large mixing bowl. Combine with oysters to include liquor. Add softened butter and light cream until fully incorporated. Add salt and pepper to taste. Bake, covered, for approximately 30 minutes and then, uncovered, for an additional 10 minutes.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix, blend and chill.
You can also add 1/4 cup chopped nuts and/or cherries.

title: ice cream in a can
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 1-pound can that has a plastic lid.
Put this 1-pound can into a 3-pound can (which also has a plastic lid).
Layer ice cream salt and crushed ice in the empty space between the cans.
Put the lid on the large can. Roll the can back and forth between 2 people for 10 minutes.

title: unique cheese fondue
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add soup and sour cream and mix well.
Heat over medium heat, then keep warm in fondue pot.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Put in blender; whip up.
If tripled, will fill blender.
A full blender makes 8 cups of punch.

title: noodle strudel
directions: Cook and drain noodles according to package instructions.
Add beaten eggs; combine all ingredients.
Blend well.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with buttered graham cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: On bottom of buttered 8 x 8-inch pan, place cooked broccoli. Next, layer the sliced chicken.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over broccoli and chicken.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill about 2 hours before serving.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese and add dry Jell-O; mix.
Add drained fruit, mix and refrigerate.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute onion, celery leaves, garlic and green pepper in oil until tender.
Add beans, broth, pepper, ham and Tabasco sauce. Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix shortening, flour, water and egg yolks.
Roll out.
Beat egg whites; glaze over crust and sprinkle with sugar.

title: whip cream pound cake
directions: Beat sugar, Crisco and eggs (one at a time) for 10 minutes. Gradually add flour, whipping cream, salt and vanilla.
Beat 10 more minutes.
Put on greased and floured tube pan.
Put in cold oven and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or longer.

title: grandma's spiced tea
directions: Bring to a boil the juices, water and sugar.
Put tea, cloves and allspices in a cloth and close with a twist tie.
Drop bag in liquid and let steep 5 minutes.
Makes 1 quart.

title: marinade for london broil
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Pour over meat and let stand 4 to 5 hours.

title: really good cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form into a ball.
Roll in 1 cup chopped nuts; chill.

title: david's favorite casserole
directions: Brown meat; add seasonings to taste.
Spread meat in flat glass pan.
Pour corn over meat.
Make 10 to 12 servings instant potatoes.
Spread over corn, covering meat and corn completely. Cut cheese into thin strips and decorate potatoes.
Heat in microwave on High until just heated through and cheese is melted.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil water and raisins 5 minutes.
Cool.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add vanilla to cooled raisin mixture and blend with shortening mixture; add nuts.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to raisin mixture and blend.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream together until smooth. Add food coloring, if desired.
May be served at room temperature or chilled.

title: chocolate surprise cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda.
Set aside.
Beat butter, brown sugar and 1/2 cup granulated sugar with mixer until light and fluffy; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture and 1/2 cup pecans, beat well.
Cover dough, refrigerate 15 minutes or until firm enough to roll into balls.
Place remaining 1/2 cup pecans and 1 tablespoon sugar in shallow dish.
Roll tablespoons full of dough around candy, cover completely; press one side into nut mixture. Place nut side up on ungreased cookie sheet.
Repeat placing three inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set and slightly cracked.
Let stand on cookie sheet two minutes. Transfer to wire rack, cool completely. Melt white chocolate and drizzle over cookies.
Let stand until set. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: spaghetti pizza deluxe
directions: In skillet, simmer onion, pepper and browned ground beef. Drain and add tomato sauce and seasoning. Cook spaghetti and drain.
Spray or grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread cooked spaghetti evenly. Add on top the ground beef and sauces.
Top with mushrooms and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then cut into squares.
(Instead of the onion, green pepper and Italian seasoning, I use 1 bag of spaghetti sauce seasoning by McCormick.)

title: easy soft lemon cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, Cool Whip, egg and lemon mixture; mix well. Mixture can be chilled for easier handling.
Drop by teaspoon in bowl of powdered sugar.
Coat dough well; form into balls.
Place balls 1 1/2 inches apart on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Let cookies cool; remove from cookie sheet. Makes 4 dozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat the
first
3 ingredients well in a mixer; add the next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add apples; add nuts and mix well. Bake in
x
14-inch
pan, a Bundt pan or layer cake pans. Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mac sausage and broccoli bake
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Cut broccoli into 1-inch pieces.
Add with remaining ingredients to dinner; mix well. Spoon mixture into 2-quart casserole; cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pea & peanut salad
directions: Mix and chill.
May use less with small amount of mayo.

title: burritos
directions: Prepare hamburger with the taco seasoning, according to directions on the envelope.
Heat refried beans.
Put about 2 tablespoons hamburger filling, 1 tablespoon beans and 1 tablespoon cheese on a hot flour tortilla.
Add 1 tablespoon hot sauce and fold up.
Garnish with lettuce, tomatoes, guacamole or additional hot sauce.

title: cherry coconut bars
directions: Mix well with hands the 2 cups flour, shortening and confectioners sugar.
Pat firmly into ungreased pan (8 x 16-inch). Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Do not brown.

title: apple pie filling mix to can
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil, then add lemon juice.
Cook until thick.
Cover apples in jars with liquid.
Seal and process in hot water bath 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cornflake cookies
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Set on hot flame and let mixture slightly boil up once, stirring all the while.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cornflakes and mix well.
Press in buttered baking pan.
Press out.
Before it cools, cut into squares.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots, unsalted.
Melt 1 stick margarine with cheese. Mix with carrots and pour into 1-quart casserole.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and add crumbled bread.
Sprinkle over carrot mixture. Bake at 400° just until bubbly.

title: black olive finger sandwiches
directions: Blend above ingredients and spread on thin sliced assorted breads.
Remove bread crusts and cut sandwiches in quarters or cut with cookie cutters.
Sandwiches may be made ahead and frozen in Tupperware for convenience.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Mix together and let stay in refrigerator overnight.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Melt the butter and brown onion, garlic and beef.
Add the tomato sauce, spices, mushrooms and 1 cup water.
Simmer and stir occasionally for 2 hours.
Add 1/2 cup water and flour to thicken.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese, then Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Put broccoli, potatoes, celery and onion in large pot.
Cover with water (not water in recipe).
Boil until potatoes are done. Boil 2 quarts of water and bouillon cubes until dissolved.

title: maraschino cherry cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually, creaming thoroughly.
Add flour, salt and baking powder together.
Sift.
Add to butter mixture alternately with liquid.
Quarter cherries and dredge with flour the cherries and nuts.
Blend into batter.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a tube pan or in 2 layer pans (well-greased and floured) at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool on cake rack.
Frost with Fluffy White Frosting.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna 10 minutes or until al dente, stirring occasionally to prevent noodles from sticking to pan.
Drain noodles, rinse in cold water and then lay them next to each other on waxed paper to dry.
Soften chopped broccoli by cooking it 5 minutes in boiling water.
Combine cheeses, vegetables, herbs and pepper in medium bowl.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, layer lasagna noodles, spread with half of the cheese mixture and half of the tomato sauce.
Repeat process, topping with noodles and covering with sauce.
Wrap dish with foil and freeze.

title: party dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with vegetable sticks or chips.

title: dad's special casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion, drain fat.
Stir in soup, milk and seasonings.
Layer half of noodles, meat and cheese in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Repeat layer, except cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese, return to oven until cheese melts.

title: spaghetti sauce with macaroni
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and tomatoes in melted margarine. In another pan brown hamburger meat.
Drain hamburger and add sauteed vegetables to meat, then add tomato sauce and stir. Simmer for 15 to 30 minutes after adding 1 teaspoon oregano.
Pour over prepared elbow macaroni for small children or regular spaghetti noodles.

title: berry-berry smoothie
directions: Whirl raspberries, strawberries and pineapple juice in a blender to combine. Add milk. Blend until smooth.

title: potato and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Squeeze excess liquid from broccoli.
In a large bowl, combine broccoli, undiluted soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes to soup mixture; toss to coat.
Grease deep 2 quart casserole.
Spoon mixture into casserole, arranging top layer of potato slices in concentric circles.
Cover and bake 1 hour. Uncover and bake 1 hour longer or until potatoes are tender and top is brown.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole.
Add rice and beef consomme.
Pour onion in last.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.
